ng-to-send-drone-to-red-planet%2Farticleshow%2F107826934.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Isro%20plans%20to%20send%20a%20rotocopter%20to%20Mars%2C%20inspired%20by%20Nasa's%20Ingenuity%20quadcopter.%20The%20rotocopter%20will%20carry%20instruments%20to%20profile%20the%20Martian%20atmosphere.%20As%20a%20follow-up%20to%20the%20Mangalyaan%20Mars%20Orbiter%20Mission%2C%20Isro%20plans%20an%20ambitious%20mission%20with%20a%20lander%2C%20rover%2C%20and%20drone.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20SCIENCE%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20SC's%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Judgement%20Affirms%20the%20Primacy%20of%20the%20Vote%20Over%20the%20Note%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F08223208%2Frupee-g9dbf1131e_1280.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20historic%20judgement%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20struck%20down%20as%20unconstitutional%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20that%20allowed%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F4250492f-d28e-471f-ab3e-565455d93d9d%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiOGd0ZHcifQ.qSmsnSAE4KRD-0ugYuOxFpZK9WPqcwSvh4eCfOgv5Os%5C%22%3Eanonymous%20donations%20to%20political%20parties%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20five-judge%20constitution%20bench%20unanimously%20quashed%20the%20high-value%20scheme%2C%20holding%20that%20it%20was%20violative%20of%20the%20right%20to%20information%20and%20thus%20contravened%20free%20speech%20and%20expression%20under%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20February%2015%20judgement%20upheld%20the%20core%20principle%20of%20democracy%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20the%20voter%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20information%20about%20who%20is%20funding%20political%20parties%20and%20their%20election%20campaigns.%C2%A0The%20court%20also%20directed%20that%20the%20sale%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20be%20stopped%20with%20immediate%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20revoked%20amendments%20made%20to%20the%20Income%20Tax%20Act%20and%20the%20Representation%20of%20People%20Act%20which%20had%20made%20the%20donations%20anonymous.%20It%20found%20the%20amendments%20to%20the%20Companies%20Act%2C%20which%20removed%20the%20condition%20that%20companies%20could%20only%20donate%20up%20to%207.5%25%20of%20their%20profit%20to%20political%20parties%20without%20disclosing%20the%20details%20of%20recipient%20parties%20in%20their%20profit%20and%20loss%20account%2C%20as%20%E2%80%9Cmanifestly%20arbitrary%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20noted%20that%20%E2%80%9Cunlimited%20corporate%20contributions%20to%20political%20parties%20is%20arbitrary%20and%20violative%20of%20Article%2014%20%5Bof%20the%20constitution%5D%2C%E2%80%9D%20which%20guarantees%20the%20right%20to%20equality%20before%20law.%20It%20added%20that%20this%20violates%20%E2%80%9Cfree%20and%20fair%20elections%E2%80%9D%C2%A0as%20it%20would%20enable%20companies%20to%20unduly%20influence%20the%20ruling%20parties%20by%20giving%20them%20huge%20contributions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20verdict%20has%20made%20a%20logical%20connection%20between%20anonymous%20corporate%20donations%20and%20the%20probability%20of%20policies%20being%20made%20to%20suit%20the%20donors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fquid-pro-quo-how-revealing-electoral-bonds-will-clear-questions-of-len-den%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Quid-Pro-Quo%E2%80%99%3A%20How%20Revealing%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Will%20Clear%20Questions%20of%20%E2%80%98Len-Den%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20had%20presented%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9Celectoral%20reform%E2%80%9D.%20The%20BJP%20defended%20it%20as%20an%20instrument%20to%20combat%20corruption%2C%20black%20money%20and%20to%20bring%20much-needed%20transparency%C2%A0to%20political%20funding.%20But%20it%20had%20done%20the%20exact%20opposite%2C%20as%20it%20allowed%20anonymous%20donors%20to%20contribute%20unlimited%20amounts%20to%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpokespersons%20of%20the%20BJP%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fopposition-hails-supreme-court-order-striking-down-electoral-bonds%5C%22%3Estill%20insist%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20electoral%20bonds%20were%20designed%20to%20promote%20transparency.%20The%20apex%20court%20rejected%20the%20contention%20that%20it%20was%20a%20way%20to%20curb%20black%20money%20in%20election%20finance%2C%20but%20this%20defence%20continues%20to%20be%20given%20even%20after%20the%20court%20has%20trashed%20this%20claim.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20this%20argument%20was%20made%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20argued%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcitizens-have-no-fundamental-right-to-know-of-source-of-political-funding-ag-to-sc%5C%22%3Ecitizens%20have%20no%20fundamental%20right%20to%20know%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20sources%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Ffcf8f085-3e4d-4c4e-aa13-474ee046e0c3%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiOGd0ZHcifQ.qSmsnSAE4KRD-0ugYuOxFpZK9WPqcwSvh4eCfOgv5Os%5C%22%3Ethe%20funding%20of%20political%20parties%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20government%20counsel%20had%20ruled%20out%20providing%20any%20information%20to%20the%20public%20regarding%20corporate%20or%20individual%20donations%20to%20parties%20on%20grounds%20of%20safeguarding%20the%20privacy%20of%20donors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20public%20would%20not%20be%20informed%20of%20who%20was%20buying%20and%20who%20was%20donating%2C%20the%20government%20could%20track%20this%20from%20the%20government-owned%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(SBI)%2C%20which%20has%20a%20list%20of%20all%20bonds%20sold%20and%20deposited%20(and%20which%20it%20now%20has%20to%20make%20public).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20the%20Court%20did%20not%20accept%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20stance%2C%20stating%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20right%20of%20a%20citizen%20to%20know%20how%20political%20parties%20are%20being%20funded%20must%20be%20balanced%20against%20the%20right%20of%20a%20person%20to%20maintain%20privacy%20of%20their%20political%20affiliations.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20before%20its%20introduction%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20and%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20(RBI)%20opposed%20the%20scheme.%20The%20ECI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felection-commission-has-no-comments-on-landmark-verdict-on-electoral-bonds-how-it-changed-its-stance%5C%22%3Ehad%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20would%20have%20%E2%80%9Ca%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F8fec65d3-c80c-4890-9ac0-49f7324c2921%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiOGd0ZHcifQ.qSmsnSAE4KRD-0ugYuOxFpZK9WPqcwSvh4eCfOgv5Os%5C%22%3Eserious%20impact%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20the%20transparency%20of%20political%20finance%2Ffunding%20of%20political%20parties%E2%80%9D%20(though%20it%20later%20altered%20its%20view)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felectoral-bonds-rbi-finance-ministry%5C%22%3Eand%20the%20RBI%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20would%20set%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbad%20precedent%E2%80%9D.%20Several%20reports%20by%20right%20to%20information%20activists%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fa9b86fc3-ae34-4a04-8078-69e9d7219713%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiOGd0ZHcifQ.qSmsnSAE4KRD-0ugYuOxFpZK9WPqcwSvh4eCfOgv5Os%5C%22%3Erevealed%20the%20opaqueness%20in%20and%20problems%20with%20the%20scheme%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcharts-electoral-bonds-supreme-court-quashed%5C%22%3EWhat%20Needs%20to%20Be%20Disclosed%20by%20March%2031%3A%205%20Charts%20to%20Gauge%20the%20Cash%20Flow%20Through%20Electoral%20Bonds%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20went%20ahead%20with%20the%20scheme%20despite%20apprehensions%20regarding%20its%20constitutional%20validity.%20The%20official%20arguments%20marshalled%20to%20defend%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20erroneous.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20voter%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20know%20has%20been%20placed%20above%20everything%20else%20as%20information%20is%20essential%20for%20democracy.%20The%20judgement%20notes%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20right%20to%20information%20of%20the%20voter%20includes%20the%20right%20to%20information%20of%20financial%20contributions%20to%20a%20political%20party%20because%20of%20the%20influence%20of%20money%20in%20electoral%20politics%20(through%20electoral%20outcomes)%20and%20governmental%20decisions%20(through%20a%20seat%20at%20the%20table%20and%20%3Cem%3Equid%20pro%20quo%3C%2Fem%3E%20arrangements%20between%20the%20contributor%20and%20the%20political%20party).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20standpoint%20of%20democracy%2C%20it%20is%20important%20for%20the%20public%20to%20get%20information%20on%20political%20funding%20so%20as%20to%20exercise%20a%20watchdog%20role.%20The%20absence%20of%20this%20information%20violates%20the%20very%20principle%20of%20an%20%E2%80%98informed%20electorate%E2%80%99.%20The%20court%20underscored%20this%20when%20it%20stated%20that%20people%20have%20the%20right%20to%20know%20who%20makes%20contributions%20to%20which%20political%20parties%20as%20the%20latter%20functions%20in%20the%20public%20realm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20elections%20are%20an%20expensive%20affair%20wholly%20funded%20by%20corporate%20donors%2C%20which%20establishes%20a%20close%20nexus%20between%20big%20capital%20and%20politics.%20Electoral%20bonds%20are%20the%20most%20significant%20institutional%20innovation%20to%20date%20to%20cement%20this%20nexus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20has%20been%20the%20biggest%20beneficiary%20of%20this%20secretive%20scheme.%20Till%20the%20end%20of%20the%20financial%20year%202022-2023%2C%20of%20the%20total%20of%20Rs%2012%2C000%20crore%20coming%20through%20this%20scheme%20since%20its%20inception%2C%20Rs%206%2C500%20crore%20went%20to%20the%20BJP%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felectoral-bonds-are-illegal-now-but-who-benefited-for-the-6-years-they-lasted%5C%22%3Ewhich%20is%20nearly%2055%25%20of%20the%20entire%20amount%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Congress%20party%20was%20way%20behind%2C%20receiving%20around%20Rs%201%2C000%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mismatch%20between%20the%20BJP%20and%20its%20nearest%20rival%20exemplifies%20the%20unequal%20playing%20field%20created%20by%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felectoral-bonds-are-illegal-now-but-who-benefited-for-the-6-years-they-lasted%5C%22%3EElectoral%20Bonds%20Are%20Illegal%20Now.%20But%20Who%20Benefitted%20for%20the%206%2B%20Years%20They%20Lasted%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElectoral%20bonds%20were%20pitched%20as%20an%20alternative%20to%20cash%20donations%20that%20would%20make%20political%20funding%20%E2%80%98cleaner%E2%80%99%20by%20encouraging%20donors%20to%20channel%20funding%20for%20political%20parties%20via%20the%20SBI.%20The%20government%E2%80%99s%20counsel%20argued%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20%5Belectoral%20bonds%5D%20scheme%20has%20been%20enacted%20in%20pursuance%20of%20a%20legitimate%20state%20interest%20%E2%80%93%20to%20shift%20from%20cash-driven%2C%20unregulated%20and%20unaccounted%20cash-based%20political%20donations%20to%20a%20regulated%2C%20digital%20and%20legal%20political%20donation%20framework.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20direct%20and%20untraceable%20cash%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20vanished.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20share%20of%20the%20income%20of%20national%20parties%20through%20unknown%20sources%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fdata%2Fparties-unknown-income-rise-despite-electoral-bonds-data%2Farticle67503811.ece%5C%22%3Eseen%20an%20increase%20since%202018%20despite%20electoral%20bonds%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20scheme%20was%20designed%20to%20give%20a%20pivotal%20advantage%20to%20the%20BJP.%20Basically%2C%20it%20was%20a%20way%20for%20the%20corporate%20sector%20to%20fund%20the%20BJP%20and%20a%20way%20to%20choke%20the%20funds%20for%20the%20opposition%20by%20shielding%20unlimited%20corporate%20donations%20to%20the%20BJP%20from%20public%20scrutiny%20while%20exposing%20all%20others%20to%20scrutiny%20by%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20double-edged%20policy%20has%20given%20the%20BJP%20a%20clear%20edge%20over%20its%20rivals.%20Coupled%20with%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20willingness%20to%20use%20enforcement%20agencies%20to%20target%20the%20opposition%2C%20electoral%20bonds%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F2e430ed7-7d40-4cd7-a6c5-e43d297ad573%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiOGd0ZHcifQ.qSmsnSAE4KRD-0ugYuOxFpZK9WPqcwSvh4eCfOgv5Os%5C%22%3Efurther%20tilt%20the%20playing%20field%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20its%20favour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20petitions%20challenged%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20in%202018%20itself%20%E2%80%93%20when%20the%20scheme%20was%20notified%20%E2%80%93%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20it%20distorts%20elections%20and%20creates%20an%20uneven%20playing%20field.%C2%A0Petitioners%20argued%20as%20early%20as%202019%20that%20the%20scheme%20allowed%20%E2%80%9Cnon-transparency%20in%20political%20funding%E2%80%9D%20and%20legitimised%20electoral%20corruption%20at%20a%20%E2%80%9Chuge%20scale%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20Bench%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20Ranjan%20Gogoi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-refuses-stay-electoral-bonds%5C%22%3Erefused%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20grant%20an%20interim%20stay.%20Likewise%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20S.A.%20Bobde%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-refuses-stay-fresh-sale-electoral-bonds-adr%5C%22%3Erejected%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20plea%20for%20the%20same%20relief.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20six%20years%20to%20conclude%C2%A0that%20the%20scheme%20was%20indeed%20unconstitutional.%20All%20the%20objections%20that%20are%20now%20accepted%20were%20articulated%20in%20those%20petitions%2C%20but%20the%20court%20refused%20to%20stay%20the%20scheme%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20debate%20around%20the%20scheme%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-electoral-bonds-interim-order%5C%22%3Eraised%20%E2%80%9Cweighty%20issues%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20needed%20time%20for%20deliberation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpart-of-secret-ballot-how-the-modi-govt-backed-electoral-bonds-in-the-supreme-court%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Part%20of%20Secret%20Ballot%E2%80%99%3A%20How%20the%20Modi%20Govt%20Backed%20Electoral%20Bonds%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20allowed%20the%20BJP%20to%20accumulate%20money%20and%20use%20these%20funds%20to%20transform%20itself%20into%20a%20dominant%20electoral%20machine.%20These%20illegal%20electoral%20bonds%20have%20already%20funded%20one%20full%20general%20election%20and%20many%20state%20elections.%20This%20includes%20the%202019%20election%2C%20which%20was%20more%20expensive%20than%20the%202016%20American%20election%20which%20brought%20Donald%20Trump%20to%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20that%20the%20apex%20court%20reserved%20its%20judgment%20in%20November%2C%20it%20allowed%20the%20BJP%20to%20collect%20two%20more%20tranches%20before%20the%20polls.%20The%20delay%20in%20resolving%20this%20vital%20constitutional%20matter%20has%20done%20immense%20damage%20to%20electoral%20democracy%20by%20giving%20a%20head%20start%20to%20the%20BJP%20over%20its%20rivals%20through%20this%20insidious%20scheme%20as%20we%20move%20towards%20the%202024%20general%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judgement%20closely%20examined%20the%20relationship%20between%20money%20and%20politics%20and%20noted%20in%20this%20context%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20primary%20way%20through%20which%20money%20directly%20influences%20politics%20is%20through%20its%20impact%20on%20electoral%20outcomes%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDisparity%20in%20access%20to%20funds%20can%20create%20political%20inequality%2C%20which%20affects%20electoral%20democracy%20by%20tilting%20public%20policy%20towards%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20super-rich%2C%20ignoring%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20majority%2C%20particularly%20the%20poor%20and%20the%20vulnerable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20structure%20of%20funding%20is%20sure%20to%20skew%20elections%20in%20favour%20of%20top%20corporates%20who%20are%20funding%20the%20BJP%20(not%20just%20its%20elections).%20As%20the%20court%20said%20in%20its%20judgement%2C%20such%20support%20can%20lead%20to%20%E2%80%98quid%20pro%20quo%20arrangements%E2%80%99%20between%20parties%20and%20donors%2C%20which%20undermine%20electoral%20democracy%20and%20governance.%20It%20can%20lead%20to%20policy%20capture%2C%20where%20decisions%20over%20policies%20are%20directed%20away%20from%20the%20public%20interest%20towards%20particular%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20landmark%20judgment%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20recent%20political%20history%2C%20is%20a%20great%20victory%20for%20democracy%20and%20transparency%2C%20and%20for%20those%20who%20have%20been%20vocal%20critics%20of%20the%20ruling%20dispensation%E2%80%99s%20corporate%20connections.%20It%20establishes%20the%20primacy%20of%20people%E2%80%99s%20power%20over%20money%20power%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98votes%20over%20notes%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComing%20just%20weeks%20before%20the%20general%20elections%2C%20it%20is%20a%20big%20setback%20for%20the%20ruling%20party%2C%20not%20the%20least%20because%20the%20court%20has%20asked%20the%20ECI%20to%20publish%20donor%20names%20and%20the%20details%20of%20political%20parties%C2%A0that%20have%20received%20the%20contributions.%20This%20will%20uncover%20the%20backdoor%20linkages%20between%20ruling%20parties%20and%20select%20corporates.%20These%20are%20well%20known.%20But%20this%20will%20give%20an%20official%20imprimatur%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERemoving%20the%20veil%20on%20corporate%20donations%20can%20dent%20the%20ruling%20party%E2%80%99s%20moral%20authority%20as%20it%20calls%20into%20question%20its%20purported%20anti-corruption%20plank%2C%20which%20it%20has%20used%20systematically%20to%20delegitimise%20and%20discredit%20the%20opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fzoya-hasan%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EZoya%20Hasan%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20Professor%20Emerita%2C%20Centre%20for%20Political%20Studies%2C%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708349716000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F08223208%2Frupee-g9dbf1131e_1280.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felectoral-bonds-primacy-vote-over-note%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20backdoor%20linkages%20between%20ruling%20parties%20and%20select%20corporates%20are%20well%20known%2C%20but%20the%20court's%20order%20asking%20the%20election%20commission%20to%20publish%20details%20around%20donor%20and%20party%20information%20will%20give%20an%20official%20imprimatur%20to%20them.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felectoral-bonds-primacy-vote-over-note%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Special%20announcement%20about%20Don%203%20on%20Feb%2020%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708349431000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107827403%2Cimgsize-30716.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fdon-3-farhan-akhtar-to-make-a-special-announcement-regarding-the-ranveer-singh-starrer-on-february-20-see-post%2Farticleshow%2F107827403.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%2