%2C%20but%20bonds%20and%20real%20estate%20would%20be%20crushed.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGambling%20on%20rate%20cuts%20has%20been%20a%20major%20theme%20in%202024%2C%20but%20as%20a%20string%20of%20hot%20economic%20data%20points%20has%20kept%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20on%20its%20toes%2C%20some%20in%20markets%20have%20begun%20to%20wonder%3A%20what%20if%20the%20Fed%20doesn't%20cut%20this%20year%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMore%20confidence%20needed%26quot%3B%20is%20the%20mantra%20Fed%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell%20has%20been%20repeating%2C%20remaining%20crystal%20clear%20about%20the%20central%20bank's%20goal%20of%20bringing%20the%20inflation%20level%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpowell-60-minutes-interview-fed-interest-rate-cuts-before-election-2024-2%5C%22%3Ecloser%20to%202%25%20target%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spike%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-economy-gdp-fourth-quarter-of-2023-2024-1%5C%22%3E3.3%25%20in%20fourth%20quarter%20GDP%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20influx%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-labor-market-unemployment-rate-wage-growth-january-economy-2024-2%5C%22%3E353%2C000%20new%20jobs%20in%20January%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-cpi-consumer-price-index-january-housing-food-energy-prices-2024-2%5C%22%3Einflation%20at%203.1%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20all%20data%20points%20that%20are%20complicating%20Fed%20policy%2C%20and%20upsetting%20markets%20eagerly%20waiting%20for%20interest%20rates%20to%20come%20down.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20few%20weeks%20of%20strong%20data%20have%20led%20some%20in%20the%20market%20to%20start%20raising%20the%20question%20of%20what%20might%20the%20impact%20be%20if%20Powell%20and%20Co.%20don't%20cut%20this%20year%2C%20or%20at%20the%20very%20least%2C%20keep%20rates%20higher%20than%20markets%20are%20hoping.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EStocks%20to%20stay%20strong%2C%20but%20bonds%20to%20suffer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EBank%20of%20America%20analysts%20said%20in%20a%20note%20this%20week%20that%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20stocks%20should%20still%20be%20favorably%20positioned%2C%20regardless%20of%20coming%20Fed%20moves.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20remind%20investors%20that%20we%20expected%20strong%20returns%20this%20year%20not%20because%20of%20what%20the%20Fed%20would%20do%20in%202024%2C%20but%20because%20of%20what%20the%20Fed%20had%20already%20accomplished%20from%20March%202022%20to%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20note%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20market%20pros%20echoed%20this%20and%20said%20that%20while%20no%20cuts%20is%20not%20a%20likely%20scenario%2C%20the%20business%20cycle%20should%20be%20supportive%20of%20continued%20gains%20regardless%20of%20policy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20an%20old%20saying%20that%20in%20the%20land%20of%20the%20blind%2C%20the%20one-eyed%20man%20is%20king.%20So%20in%20a%20relative%20sense%2C%20the%20outperformers%20in%20this%20environment%20will%20likely%20be%20healthcare%20and%20then%20consumer%20staples%2C%26quot%3B%20David%20Rosenberg%2C%20economist%20and%20the%20founder%20of%20Rosenberg%20Research%2C%20told%20Business%20insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20bonds%2C%20higher-for-longer%20would%20be%20a%20different%20story.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERosenberg%20said%20there's%2090%25%20correlation%20between%20expectations%20for%20monetary%20policy%20and%20longer-term%20treasury%20bond%20yields%2C%20emphasizing%20that%20investors%20could%20see%20the%2010-year%20Treasury%20tick%20back%20up%20to%204.7%25%2C%20not%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20the%20multi-decade%20highs%20seen%20at%20the%20end%20of%20last%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20continuation%20of%20higher%20interest%20rates%20also%20poses%20potential%20downside%20risks%20for%20bank%20stocks%2C%20BofA%20analysts%20said%20in%20a%20separate%20note.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20that%20keeps%20investors%20on%20guard%20is%20banks'%20holdings%20of%20many%20lower-yielding%20bonds.%20Those%20bonds%2C%20which%20offer%20low%20returns%2C%20can't%20offset%20the%20banks'%20higher%20funding%20costs%20in%20a%20high-interest%20rate%20environment%2C%20creating%20a%20%26quot%3Bnegative%20carry%26quot%3B%20risk%2C%20the%20analysts%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20stronger%20economy%20would%20imply%20healthier%20credit%20quality%2C%20better%20growth.%20However%2C%20we%20believe%20investors%20are%20concerned%20about%20a%20prolonged%20period%20of%20tight%20monetary%20policy%20(higher%20for%20longer%20rates%2C%20QT)%20given%20'perceived'%20liquidity-related%20risks%2C%26quot%3B%20BofA%20analysts%20said%20in%20the%20note.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERosenberg%20echoed%20the%20potential%20risks%20to%20the%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20%5Bthe%20Fed%5D%20doesn't%20cut%20rates%20because%20it%20remains%20concerned%20over%20inflation%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20the%20economy%2C%20it%20is%20going%20to%20be%20decisively%20negative%20for%20the%20bank%20stocks%2C%26quot%3B%20Rosenberg%20added.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EMore%20pain%20for%20real%20estate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20sector%20that's%20been%20battered%20by%20the%20Fed's%20rate-hike%20campaign%20has%20been%20commercial%20real%20estate%2C%20and%20any%20delay%20in%20cutting%20would%20prolong%20the%20pain%20being%20felt%20in%20that%20sector.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20wall%20of%20debt%20maturities%20is%20coming%20for%20commercial%20property%20owners%20this%20year%20and%20beyond%2C%20and%20landlords%20in%20many%20cases%20will%20be%20refinancing%20debt%20at%20higher%20rates%20and%20lower%20property%20valuations.%20The%20office%20sector%20in%20particular%20is%20in%20a%20dire%20state%20as%20remote%20work%20persists%20and%20property%20values%20plunge.%20Last%20month%2C%20real%20estate%20billionaire%20Barry%20Sternlicht%20said%20the%20office%20market%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsi