ations.%20Buy-side%20estimates%20for%20Nvidia%20stand%209%25%20above%20consensus%2C%20at%20%2421.7%20billion%20for%20the%20fourth%20quarter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20dampens%20the%20potential%20for%20Nvidia%20to%20beat%20expectations%2C%20leaving%20the%20firm%20vulnerable%20to%20an%2011%25%20implied%20post-earnings%20move%2C%20Arya%20wrote%2C%20citing%20Bloomberg%20options.%20As%20of%20Friday%20afternoon%2C%20the%20stock%20stands%20at%20about%20%24740.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20decline%20could%20be%20notable%2C%20it%20would%20also%20be%20brief%2C%20he%20wrote.%20Arya%20believes%20Nvidia's%20failure%20to%20meet%20bullish%20estimates%20would%20come%20from%20supply-side%20factors%2C%20instead%20of%20more%20concerning%20shifts%20in%20demand%20and%20competition.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20volatility%20should%20resolve%20after%20Nvidia's%20upcoming%20GPU%20Tech%20Conference%2C%20set%20for%20mid-March.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20reference%20NVDA%20stock%20was%20on%20average%206%25%20higher%20(vs.%20SPX%20up%201%25)%20T%2B1%20days%20following%20the%20last%20six%20annual%20GTC%20events%2C%26quot%3B%20Arya%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENvidia%20has%20remained%20a%20compelling%20stock%2C%20with%20its%20valuation%20at%2035x%20its%20price-to-earnings%20ratio%2C%20below%20its%20median.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShares%20of%20the%20semiconductor%20manufacturer%20have%20surged%20astronomically%2C%20helping%20the%20company%20eclipse%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Famzn-stock%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fgoogl-stock%5C%22%3EAlphabet%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20become%20the%20third%20most%20valued%20firm%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fs%26amp%3Bp_500%3Futm_source%3Dmarkets%26utm_medium%3Dingest%253Futm_source%253Dmarkets%26utm_medium%3Dingest%26utm_medium%3Dingest%26utm_source%3Dmarkets%26utm_medium%3Dinge