ed-to-such-a-big-name-and-if-it-ever-helped-her-career%2Farticleshow%2F107826757.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chanda%20Kochhar%2C%20Husband's%20Arrest%20By%20CBI%20%26quot%3BAmounts%20To%20Abuse%20Of%20Power%26quot%3B%3A%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20arrest%20of%20ICICI%20Bank's%20former%20Managing%20Director%20and%20Chief%20Executive%20Officer%20(CEO)%20Chanda%20Kochhar%20and%20her%20husband%20Deepak%20Kochhar%20by%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI)%20in%20a%20loan%20fraud%20case%20was%20%26quot%3Bwithout%20application%20of%20mind%20and%20due%20regard%20to%20the%20law%26quot%3B%2C%20amounting%20to%20an%20%26quot%3Babuse%20of%20power%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20Bombay%20High%20Court%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20division%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Anuja%20Prabhudessai%20and%20N%20R%20Borkar%20had%20on%20February%206%20held%20the%20Kochhars'%20arrest%20as%20illegal%20and%20confirmed%20a%20January%202023%20interim%20order%20passed%20by%20another%20bench%20granting%20them%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20order%20made%20available%20on%20Monday%2C%20the%20court%20said%20the%20CBI%20has%20been%20unable%20to%20demonstrate%20the%20existence%20of%20circumstances%20or%20supportive%20material%20based%20on%20which%20the%20decision%20to%20arrest%20was%20taken.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20absence%20of%20such%20circumstances%20renders%20the%20arrest%20illegal%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuch%20routine%20arrest%20without%20application%20of%20mind%20and%20due%20regard%20to%20the%20law%20amounts%20to%20an%20abuse%20of%20power%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20refused%20to%20accept%20the%20probe%20agency's%20contention%20that%20the%20arrest%20was%20made%20as%20the%20Kochhars%20were%20not%20cooperating%20with%20the%20probe%20and%20said%20the%20accused%20had%20a%20right%20to%20remain%20silent%20during%20interrogation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20right%20to%20silence%20emanates%20from%20Article%2020(3)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%2C%20which%20gives%20an%20accused%20the%20right%20against%20self-incrimination.%20Suffice%20it%20to%20say%20that%20exercise%20of%20the%20right%20to%20remain%20silent%20cannot%20be%20equated%20with%20non-cooperation%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said%20in%20the%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CBI%20arrested%20the%20couple%20on%20December%2023%2C%202022%2C%20in%20the%20Videocon-ICICI%20Bank%20loan%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20immediately%20moved%20the%20high%20court%20challenging%20the%20arrest%20and%20sought%20for%20the%20same%20to%20be%20declared%20illegal%2C%20and%20by%20way%20of%20interim%20order%2C%20sought%20to%20be%20released%20on%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%209%2C%202023%2C%20the%20court%2C%20in%20an%20interim%20order%2C%20granted%20the%20Kochhars%20bail%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20CBI%20had%20made%20the%20arrest%20casually%20and%20mechanically%20and%20without%20application%20of%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20February%206%20order%2C%20the%20bench%20noted%20that%20section%2041A%20of%20the%20Criminal%20Procedure%20Code%20(CrPC)%20was%20introduced%20to%20avoid%20routine%20arrests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20cited%20that%20this%20provision%20restricts%20the%20power%20to%20arrest%20when%20an%20accused%20person%20complies%20with%20the%20notice%20issued%20by%20the%20police%20to%20appear%20for%20questioning%20and%20mandates%20that%20an%20arrest%20shall%20be%20made%20only%20when%20the%20police%20are%20of%20the%20opinion%20that%20it%20is%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20held%20that%20while%20it%20was%20within%20the%20domain%20of%20the%20investigating%20agency%20to%20interrogate%20an%20accused%20and%20to%20arrive%20at%20a%20subjective%20satisfaction%20on%20the%20issue%2C%20the%20same%20was%20not%20%26quot%3Bwholly%20immune%20from%20judicial%20reviewability%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20court%20can%20consider%20whether%20the%20reasons%20for%20deprivation%20of%20liberty%20are%20rational%2C%20reasonable%20or%20fanciful%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20further%20said%20that%20the%20first%20information%20report%20(FIR)%20against%20the%20Kochhars%20was%20registered%20in%202019%2C%20and%20they%20were%20summoned%20for%20questioning%20only%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDespite%20the%20gravity%20of%20the%20offence%2C%20the%20petitioners%20(Kochhars)%20were%20not%20interrogated%20or%20summoned%20for%20a%20period%20of%20over%20three%20years%20from%20the%20date%20of%20registration%20of%20the%20crime%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20June%202022%2C%20the%20Kochhars%20have%20been%20appearing%20before%20the%20CBI%20as%20and%20when%20notices%20under%20section%2041A%20were%20issued%20to%20them%2C%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CBI%20had%20claimed%20that%20the%20Kochhars%20were%20arrested%20as%20they%20were%20not%20cooperating%20with%20the%20probe%20and%20that%20their%20custodial%20interrogation%20was%20required%20to%20unearth%20the%20entire%20gamut%20of%20conspiracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20the%20Kochhars%2C%20the%20CBI%20had%20also%20arrested%20Videocon%20group%20founder%20Venugopal%20Dhoot%20in%20the%20case.%20The%20high%20court%20granted%20him%20bail%20in%20January%202023%20in%20its%20interim%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20probe%20agency%20has%20alleged%20that%20private%20sector%20lender%20ICICI%20Bank%20had%20sanctioned%20credit%20facilities%20to%20the%20tune%20of%20Rs%203%2C250%20crore%20to%20the%20companies%20of%20Videocon%20Group%20promoted%20by%20Dhoot%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20Banking%20Regulation%20Act%2C%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India's%20guidelines%2C%20and%20credit%20policy%20of%20the%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CBI%20had%20named%20the%20Kochhars%2C%20Dhoot%20along%20with%20Nupower%20Renewables%20(NRL)%20managed%20by%20Deepak%20Kochhar%2C%20Supreme%20Energy%2C%20Videocon%20International%20Electronics%20Ltd%20and%20Videocon%20Industries%20Ltd%20as%20accused%20in%20the%20FIR%20registered%20in%202019%20under%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20sections%20related%20to%20criminal%20conspiracy%20and%20provisions%20of%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Corruption%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20has%20alleged%20that%20the%20ICICI%20Bank%20sanctioned%20credit%20facilities%20to%20the%20tune%20of%20Rs%203%2C250%20crore%20to%20these%20companies%20in%20violation%20of%20norms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20further%20claimed%20that%20as%20a%20part%20of%20quid%20pro%20quo%2C%20Dhoot%20made%20an%20investment%20of%20Rs%2064%20crore%20in%20Nupower%20Renewables%20through%20Supreme%20Energy%20Pvt%20Ltd%20(SEPL)%20and%20transferred%20SEPL%20to%20Pinnacle%20Energy%20Trust%20managed%20by%20Deepak%20Kochhar%20through%20a%20circuitous%20route%20between%202010%20and%202012.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708347360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-12%2Flvkn7gpg_chanda-kochhar_625x300_24_December_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ficici-bank-ex-ceo-chanda-kochhar-husband-deepak-kochhars-arrest-by-cbi-amounts-to-abuse-of-power-bombay-high-court-5087762%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20arrest%20of%20ICICI%20Bank's%20former%20Managing%20Director%20and%20Chief%20Executive%20Officer%20(CEO)%20Chanda%20Kochhar%20and%20her%20husband%20Deepak%20Kochhar%20by%20the%20CBI%20in%20a%20loan%20fraud%20case%20was%20%26quot%3Bwithout%20application%20of%20mind%20and%20due%20regard%20to%20the%20law%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ficici-bank-ex-ceo-chanda-kochhar-husband-deepak-kochhars-arrest-by-cbi-amounts-to-abuse-of-power-bombay-high-court-5087762%22%2C%22c