nxiety-stress-mental-health-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estruggling%20to%20handle%20stress%20at%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20according%20to%20a%20psychology%20professor%2C%20this%20is%20largely%20because%20this%20generation%20has%20grown%20up%20without%20work-life%20boundaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKathleen%20Pike%2C%20who%20teaches%20at%3Cspan%3E%20Columbia%20University%20and%20is%20president%20and%20CEO%20of%20One%20Mind%20at%20Work%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20older%20generations%20didn%E2%80%99t%20face%20the%20same%20technology-induced%20pressures%20at%20the%20start%20of%20their%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20they%20%5Bolder%20generations%5D%20started%20out%2C%20it%20was%20a%20completely%20different%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20written%20about%20Gen%20Z%20needing%20to%20take%20more%20time%20off%20and%20not%20having%20the%20resilience%20to%20endure%20and%20reliably%20push%20through%20in%20certain%20work%20contexts.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E50%20years%20ago%2C%20when%20the%20senior%20executives%20were%20starting%20out%2C%20they%20drove%20to%20work%2C%20and%20there%20was%20no%20cellphone%2C%20there%20was%20no%20internet%2C%20there%20was%20no%20FedEx%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPike%20pointed%20to%20technology%20as%20the%20culprit%20behind%20younger%20professionals%E2%80%99%20struggles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20%26quot%3Bnothing%20was%20instantaneous%2C%20and%20when%20they%20%5Bworkers%5D%20went%20home%2C%20they%20were%20not%20reachable.%20So%20there%20was%20a%20natural%20macro%20structure%20that%20created%20lots%20of%20downtime%20that%20has%20completely%20evaporated%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20Gen%20Z%20is%20trying%20to%20create%20a%20clearer%20divide%20between%20their%20work%20and%20personal%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPart%20of%20what%20we're%20seeing%20is%20Gen%20Z%20is%20trying%20to%20put%20some%20boundaries%20back%20in%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20Pike%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%E2%80%99s%20a%20clear%20generational%20distinction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20young%20professionals%20are%20turning%20to%20trends%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fact-your-wage-trend-tiktok-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bact%20your%20wage%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%C2%A0%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-quiet-quitting-work-ethic-millennials-money-struggles-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bquiet%20quitting%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20essentially%2C%20doing%20the%20bare%20minimum%20to%20keep%20their%20job%20but%20to%20avoid%20burning%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Gen%20Z%20is%20normalizing%20the%20conversation%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-stress-anxiety-normal-life-experiences-expert-says-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emental%20health%20at%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Pike%20said%20that%20they%E2%80%99re%20sometimes%20forgetting%20the%20distinction%20between%20normal%20emotions%20and%20mental%20illness.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFeeling%20stressed%20or%20anxious%20can%20be%20useful%20indicators%20to%20help%20you%20complete%20tasks%20but%20are%20not%20always%20signs%20of%20serious%20mental%20illness%2C%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuccess%20grows%20out%20of%20learning%20how%20to%20get%20back%20on%20the%20horse%2C%20learning%20how%20to%20build%20the%20skills%2C%20how%20to%20ask%20for%20help%2C%20and%20how%20to%20build%20capacity%20in%20ways%20that%20didn't%20exist.%20That's%20part%20of%20maturing%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-pressure-work-life-technology-no-boundaries-psychologist-2024%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708344294000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d32962f533b039a885119f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-pressure-work-life-technology-no-boundaries-psychologist-2024%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Older%20generations%20didn't%20face%20the%20same%20technology-induced%20pressures%20at%20the%20start%20of%20their%20career%2C%20a%20prominent%20psychology%20professor%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sbhaimiya%40insider.com%20(Sawdah%20Bhaimiya)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-pressure-work-life-technology-no-boundaries-psychologist-2024%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BWhy%20Did%20You%20Put%20X%20Mark%3F%26quot%3B%20Supreme%20Court%20Pulls%20Up%20Chandigarh%20Poll%20Officer%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ETaking%20a%20strict%20view%20of%20the%20alleged%20defacement%20of%20ballot%20papers%20during%20the%20Chandigarh%20mayoral%20election%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20said%20that%20the%20returning%20officer%2C%20Anil%20Masih%2C%20should%20be%20prosecuted%20for%20%26quot%3Binterfering%20with%20the%20election%20process%26quot%3B.%20The%20court%20said%20this%20after%20seeking%20answers%20from%20Mr%20Masih%2C%20marking%20the%20first%20time%20in%20the%20history%20of%20independent%20India%20that%20a%20returning%20officer%20has%20been%20cross-examined%20by%20the%20country's%20Chief%20Justice.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConducting%20a%20hearing%20on%20a%20petition%20on%20the%20alleged%20irregularities%20in%20the%20election%20on%20Monday%2C%20a%20day%20after%20three%20AAP%20councillors%20switched%20over%20to%20the%20BJP%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20also%20said%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bhorsetrading%26quot%3B%20that%20is%20going%20on%20is%20a%20serious%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20has%20asked%20for%20the%20ballot%20papers%20to%20be%20brought%20to%20it%20for%20examination%20on%20Tuesday.%20After%20initially%20proposing%20that%2C%20instead%20of%20carrying%20out%20a%20fresh%20election%2C%20the%20votes%20must%20be%20counted%20afresh%20by%20a%20new%20returning%20officer%2C%20the%20court%20said%20that%20it%20will%20decide%20on%20the%20issue%20after%20examining%20the%20ballot%20papers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20counting%20of%20the%20mayoral%20election%20on%20January%2030%2C%20eight%20votes%20had%20been%20declared%20invalid%20by%20returning%20officer%20Anil%20Masih%20and%20the%20AAP's%20mayoral%20candidate%2C%20Kuldeep%20Kumar%2C%20had%20been%20defeated%20by%20Manoj%20Sonkar%20of%20the%20BJP%20with%20a%20margin%20of%20four%20votes.%20The%20AAP%20had%20claimed%20that%20Mr%20Masih%20-%20a%20member%20of%20the%20BJP's%20minority%20cell%20-%20had%20deliberately%20invalidated%20the%20votes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20video%20had%20emerged%20of%20Mr%20Masih%20writing%20on%20the%20ballot%20papers%20of%20some%20AAP%20councillors%20while%20looking%20at%20the%20camera%2C%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20called%20his%20action%20a%20%26quot%3Bmockery%20of%20democracy%26quot%3B%20during%20a%20hearing%20on%20February%205.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Answer%20Truthfully'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20hearing%20on%20Monday%2C%20the%20bench%20of%20Chief%20Justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%2C%20JB%20Pardiwala%20and%20Manoj%20Misra%20took%20note%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20BJP's%20Manoj%20Sonkar%20had%20resigned%20as%20mayor%20the%20previous%20evening%20and%20then%20asked%20Mr%20Masih%20to%20come%20forward%20and%20answer%20a%20few%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CMr%20Masih%2C%20I%20am%20asking%20you%20questions.%20If%20you%20don't%20give%20truthful%20answers%2C%20you%20will%20be%20prosecuted.%20This%20is%20a%20serious%20matter.%20We%20have%20seen%20the%20video.%20What%20were%20you%20doing%20looking%20at%20the%20camera%20and%20putting%20cross%20marks%20on%20the%20ballot%20papers%3F%20Why%20were%20you%20putting%20the%20marks%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdmitting%20that%20he%20had%20put%20cross%20(X)%20marks%20on%20eight%20ballot%20papers%2C%20Mr%20Masih%20responded%20that%20he%20had%20done%20so%20because%20the%20ballot%20papers%20that%20were%20defaced%20had%20to%20be%20segregated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhy%20did%20you%20(Mr%20Masih)%20deface%20the%20ballot%20papers%3F%20You%20only%20had%20to%20sign%20the%20papers.%20Where%20is%20it%20provided%20in%20the%20rules%20that%20you%20can%20put%20other%20marks%20on%20the%20ballot%20papers%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20then%20turned%20to%20Solicitor%20General%20of%20India%20Tushar%20Mehta%2C%20who%20was%20representing%20the%20Chandigarh%20Administration%2C%20and%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CMr%20Solicitor%2C%20he%20(Mr%20Masih)%20has%20to%20be%20prosecuted.%20He%20is%20interfering%20with%20the%20election%20process.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Returning%20Officer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELaying%20out%20the%20next%20steps%20the%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20propose%20to%20do%20is%20this.%20We%20will%20direct%20the%20Deputy%20Commissioner%20to%20appoint%20a%20fresh%20returning%20officer%2C%20who%20is%20not%20aligned%20to%20any%20political%20party.%20The%20process%20shall%20be%20taken%20to%20the%20logical%20conclusion%20from%20the%20stage%20it%20stopped%20before%20the%20declaration%20of%20results.%20Let%20the%20results%20be%20declared%20disregarding%20any%20mark%20put%20by%20the%20returning%20officer.%20Let%20the%20process%20be%20overseen%20judicially%20by%20the%20high%20court.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESolicitor%20General%20Mehta%20said%20he%20had%20been%20told%20that%20some%20of%20the%20ballot%20papers%20were%20torn%20or%20defaced%20and%20that%20the%20high%20court%20should%20see%20them.%20Responding%20to%20this%2C%20the%20lawyer%20for%20the%20petitioner%20in%20the%20case%20-%20AAP's%20Kuldeep%20Kumar%20-%20claimed%20only%20eight%20ballot%20papers%20needed%20to%20be%20seen%20and%20that%20they%20were%20not%20torn.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20then%20said%20it%20would%20examine%20the%20ballot%20papers%20and%20asked%20for%20them%20to%20be%20presented%20before%20it%2C%20with%20adequate%20security%2C%20on%20Tuesday.%20It%20also%20asked%20Mr%20Masih%20to%20be%20present.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20request%20was%20made%20that%20the%20matter%20be%20heard%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20process%20of%20horsetrading%20which%20is%20going%20on%20is%20a%20serious%20matter.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20said%20it%20would%20decide%20on%20whether%20fresh%20elections%20would%20be%20conducted%20or%20the%20earlier%20votes%20would%20be%20counted%20after%20examining%20the%20ballot%20papers%20on%20Tuesday.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708344240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fot2q6i6o_chandigarh-poll-officer-1200_625x300_05_February_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fofficer-admits-he-tampered-ballots-must-be-prosecuted-orders-supreme-court-in-chandigarh-vote-count-row-5086840%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Taking%20a%20strict%20view%20of%20the%20alleged%20defacement%20of%20ballot%20papers%20during%20the%20Chandigarh%20mayoral%20election%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20said%20that%20the%20returning%20officer%2C%20Anil%20Masih%2C%20should%20be%20prosecuted.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fofficer-admits-he-tampered-ballots-must-be-prosecuted-orders-supreme-court-in-chandigarh-vote-count-row-5086840%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Electoral%20Bonds-Beyond%20The%20Supreme%20Court's%20Brake%2C%20A%20Few%20Questions%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-10%2Ftthv9vd8_supreme-court-india-generic-pti_625x300_10_October_22.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Fnews%2Fnews%2Felectoral-bonds-to-be-stopped-immediately-says-supreme-court-761865%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court's%20recent%20decision%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20strike%20down%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Felectoral-bonds-verdict-supreme-court-on-electoral-bonds-verdict-weighing-options-no-ordinance-yet-sources-5070428%23%3A~%3Atext%3DElectoral%2520bonds%2520are%2520financial%2520instruments%2Cto%2520make%2520political%2520funding%2520clean.%5C%22%3Eelectoral%20bonds%3C%2Fa%3E%20scheme%20introduced%20in%202016-17%20has%20undone%20the%20most%20significant%20change%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Fnews%2Fthe-big-fight%2Fwill-ban-on-electoral-bonds-clean-up-indian-politics-762177%5C%22%3Eelectoral%20finance%3C%2Fa%3E%20laws%20in%20recent%20years.%20Central%20to%20the%20court's%20decision%20is%20the%20tension%20between%20privacy%20and%20disclosure%2C%20a%20tension%20that%20animates%20all%20laws%20on%20electoral%20funding.%20While%20voters%20have%20a%20right%20to%20know%20about%20their%20candidates%20and%20parties%2C%20donors%20also%20need%20some%20privacy%20of%20political%20affiliation%20to%20express%20their%20support%20freely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Felection-bonds-worth-rs-16-000-crore-sold-till-2022-who-got-how-much-5062408%5C%22%3EElectoral%20bonds%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20now%20a%20defunct%20financial%20instrument%2C%20were%20designed%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhat-is-an-electoral-bond-5062184%5C%22%3Eanonymous%20bearer%20instruments%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20issued%20exclusively%20by%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India.%20These%20bonds%2C%20accessible%20to%20Indian%20citizens%20and%20entities%20and%20redeemable%20by%20political%20parties%20meeting%20certain%20vote%20thresholds%2C%20ostensibly%20aimed%20at%20streamlining%20political%20donations%20by%20directing%20them%20through%20formal%20banking%20channels.%20The%20introduction%20of%20these%20bonds%20was%20accompanied%20by%20a%20reduction%20in%20the%20limit%20for%20cash%20donations.%20Bonds%20were%20issued%20in%20specific%20denominations%20ranging%20from%20Rs.%201%2C000%20to%20Rs.%201%20crore%20and%20were%20valid%20for%20a%20period%20of%2015%20days%20from%20the%20date%20of%20issuance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20introducing%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Felectoral-bonds-supreme-court-electoral-bonds-verdict-today-the-scheme-the-questions-and-the-defence-5060924%5C%22%3Escheme%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20former%20Finance%20Minister%20Arun%20Jaitley%20had%20argued%2C%20%E2%80%9CDonors%20have%20also%20expressed%20reluctance%20in%20donating%20by%20cheque%20or%20other%20transparent%20methods%20as%20it%20would%20disclose%20their%20identity%20and%20entail%20adverse%20consequences%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D.%20However%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20had%20opposed%20the%20scheme%20strongly%20as%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20providing%20confidentiality%20of%20contributions%20through%20bearer%20bonds%2C%20the%20legislative%20changes%20that%20introduced%20the%20scheme%20also%20removed%20requirements%20imposed%20on%20companies%20to%20disclose%20their%20contributions%20in%20their%20annual%20accounts.%20In%20addition%2C%20these%20changes%20also%20removed%20the%20earlier%20limit%20on%20corporate%20donations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EWhy%20The%20SC%20Struck%20Down%20The%20Scheme%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-courts-big-verdict-on-electoral-bonds-scheme-today-5060171%5C%22%3Ecourt%20struck%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20scheme%20on%20two%20grounds.%20First%2C%20it%20held%20that%20the%20scheme%20did%20not%20adequately%20balance%20informational%20privacy%20with%20the%20right%20of%20voters%20to%20information%20about%20political%20parties%20and%20their%20donors.%20In%20the%20court%2C%20the%20government%20had%20submitted%20that%20informational%20privacy%20is%20important%20for%20free%20political%20expression.%20The%20petitioners%20on%20the%20other%20hand%20had%20argued%20that%20voters%20have%20a%20right%20to%20relevant%20information%20about%20their%20candidates.%20While%20the%20court%20accepted%20the%20need%20for%20informational%20privacy%20of%20political%20affiliation%20as%20an%20important%20value%2C%20it%20held%20that%20under%20the%20scheme%2C%20while%20donors%20were%20assured%20of%20complete%20confidentiality%2C%20voters%20would%20never%20know%20the%20details%20of%20donors%20and%20contributions%20through%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20reasoned%20that%20other%20existing%20mechanisms%20like%20electoral%20trusts%20maintain%20this%20balance%20much%20better.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20trusts%2C%20the%20details%20of%20donors%20are%20known%20and%20the%20details%20of%20recipient%20political%20parties%20are%20known%2C%20but%20there%20is%20no%20way%20to%20know%20which%20donor%20contributed%20to%20which%20party%2C%20since%20the%20contribution%20is%20made%20by%20the%20trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecondly%2C%20the%20court%20found%20the%20removal%20of%20limits%20on%20corporate%20donations%20under%20the%20Companies%20Act%20to%20be%20arbitrary%2C%20reasoning%20that%20equating%20corporate%20entities%20with%20individuals%20in%20the%20context%20of%20political%20contributions%20ignores%20the%20disproportionate%20financial%20influence%20of%20corporations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EOn%20The%20Confidentiality%20Issue%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20of%20the%20court%20leaves%20campaign%20finance%20laws%20in%20the%20same%20state%20it%20was%20before%202017-18.%20Contributions%20below%20a%20threshold%20of%20Rs.%2020%2C000%20do%20not%20have%20to%20be%20accounted%20for%20by%20political%20parties%2C%20companies%20are%20subject%20to%20the%20overall%20limit%20of%207.5%25%20profits%2C%20and%20the%20erstwhile%20disclosure%20requirements%20have%20been%20restored.%20The%20court's%20decision%20restores%20transparency%20requirements%20and%20also%20reduces%20the%20specific%20kind%20of%20confidentiality%20that%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20sought%20to%20provide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20theory%2C%20the%20confidentiality%20of%20political%20affiliation%20has%20significant%20value%20in%20competitive%20politics.%20The%20court%20in%20its%20judgment%20agrees%20with%20the%20importance%20of%20this%20value.%20Confidentiality%20allows%20citizens%20to%20vote%20with%20their%20money%20discreetly.%20This%20is%20an%20important%20part%20of%20the%20free%20exercise%20of%20political%20preferences.%20However%2C%20in%20practice%2C%20this%20confidentiality%20was%20not%20complete.%20As%20investigative%20reports%20found%2C%20each%20electoral%20bond%20had%20a%20serial%20number%20that%20can%20be%20tracked%20to%20identify%20its%20purchaser%2C%20raising%20concerns%20about%20confidentiality.%C2%A0This%20when%20the%C2%A0objective%20of%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20was%20to%C2%A0ease%20the%20reluctance%C2%A0of%20donors%20from%20donating%20through%20formal%20channels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20attempted%20to%20move%20money%20through%20formal%20banking%20channels%20and%20reduce%20the%20prevalence%20of%20cash%2C%20but%20for%20all%20practical%20purposes%2C%20it%20ended%20up%20giving%20asymmetric%20informational%20power%20to%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EA%20Complex%20Picture%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDid%20this%20create%20a%20serious%20imbalance%20of%20power%20between%20the%20ruling%20party%20and%20the%20opposition%3F%20An%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%20report%20found%20that%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20received%20more%20than%20half%20of%20all%20contributions%20made%20through%20electoral%20bonds.%20This%20points%20to%20a%20clear%20lop-sided%20benefit%20to%20the%20ruling%20party.%20Was%20the%20BJP%20the%20sole%20beneficiary%20of%20electoral%20bonds%3F%20On%20this%2C%20data%20by%20ADR%20presents%20a%20mixed%20picture.%20While%2052%25%20of%20BJP's%20total%20reported%20donations%20came%20from%20electoral%20bonds%20between%20FY%202016-17%20and%20FY%202021-22%2C%20for%20the%20Congress%2C%2061.54%25%20came%20from%20electoral%20bonds.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20All%20India%20Trinamool%20Congress%20received%2093%25%20of%20its%20reported%20donations%20through%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20and%20the%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%20(BJD)%20and%20the%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20(DMK)%2090%25%20each.%20While%20the%20BJP%20clearly%20benefited%20the%20most%2C%20many%20major%20parties%20profited%20from%20the%20opacity%20of%20the%20scheme.%20The%20important%20question%20is%20counterfactual%20-%20how%20much%20more%20would%20opposition%20parties%20have%20received%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20were%20it%20not%20for%20the%20potential%20ability%20of%20the%20government%20to%20learn%20the%20identities%20of%20contributors%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELastly%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20decision%20has%20two%20additional%20consequences%3A%20it%20reinstates%20spending%20caps%20on%20corporate%20donations%2C%20likely%20leading%20to%20a%20resurgence%20of%20smaller%2C%20undisclosed%20contributions%2C%20and%20it%20negates%20the%20modest%20advancements%20made%20in%20promoting%20formal%20banking%20channels%20for%20political%20donations.%20In%20essence%2C%20while%20the%20judgment%20rectifies%20informational%20imbalances%2C%20it%20does%20not%20offer%20a%20comprehensive%20solution%20to%20the%20complexities%20of%20electoral%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Anirudh%20Burman%20is%20a%20Fellow%20and%20Associate%20Research%20Director%20at%20Carnegie%20India.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708344120000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2020-11%2Fmpbfnv4_election-generic-afp650_625x300_02_November_20.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-electoral-bonds-beyond-the-supreme-courts-brake-a-few-questions-5087347%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court's%20order%20corrects%20informational%20imbalances%2C%20but%20it%20negates%20the%20modest%20advancements%20made%20in%20promoting%20formal%20banking%20channels%20for%20political%20donations.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-electoral-bonds-beyond-the-supreme-courts-brake-a-few-questions-5087347%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-electoral-bonds-beyond-the-supreme-courts-brake-a-few-questions-5087347%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-electoral-bonds-beyond-the-supreme-courts-brake-a-few-questions-5087347%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20Stays%20Proceedings%20Against%20Siddaramaiah%2C%20Others%20in%20the%202022%20Protest%20March%20Case%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F18164526%2FFwBN2HcakAEGvBw.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20stayed%20proceedings%20in%20a%20criminal%20case%20in%20which%20Karnataka%20chief%20minister%20Siddaramaiah%20is%20named%20as%20an%20accused.%20The%202022%20case%20pertains%20to%20a%20protest%20march%20held%20by%20Siddaramaih%20and%20other%20Congress%20leaders%20demanding%20the%20resignation%20of%20K.S.%20Eshwarappa%2C%20the%20then%20minister%20in%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20government%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20division%20Bench%20of%20Justice%20Hrishikesh%20Roy%20and%20Justice%20P.K.%20Mishra%2C%20however%2C%20refused%20to%20quash%20the%20criminal%20case%20against%20Siddaramaiah%20and%20Congress%20general%20secretary%20and%20Karnataka%20in-charge%20Randeep%20Singh%20Surjewala%2C%20state%20ministers%20M.B.%20Patil%20and%20Ramalinga%20Reddy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%2C%20however%2C%20stayed%20a%20Karnataka%20high%20court%20order%2C%20which%20had%20imposed%20a%20fine%20of%20Rs%2010%2C000%20each%20on%20the%20accused%20and%20had%20directed%20them%20to%20appear%20before%20a%20special%20court%20on%20March%206.%20The%20top%20court%2C%20however%2C%20issued%20notices%20to%20the%20Karnataka%20government%20and%20the%20complainant%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIssue%20notice%2C%20returnable%20in%20six%20weeks%2C%20Till%20further%20orders%2C%20%5Bthere%20shall%20be%20a%5D%20stay%20of%20proceedings%20and%20impugned%20order%20%5Bof%20Karnataka%20High%20Court%5D%20against%20the%20petitioners%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20said%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barandbench.com%2Fnews%2Fsupreme-court-stays-proceedings-case-against-karnataka-cm-siddaramaiah-2022-protest-march%5C%22%3EBar%20and%20Bench%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20dates%20back%20to%20February%202022%2C%20when%20Siddaramaiah%20and%20others%20were%20detained%20for%20holding%20a%20protest%20to%20demand%20the%20resignation%20and%20arrest%20of%20Eshwarappa%2C%20following%20the%20death%20by%20suicide%20of%20contractor%20Santosh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20advocates%20Kapil%20Sibal%2C%20Abhishek%20Manu%20Singhvi%2C%20Devadatt%20Kamat%2C%20and%20Siddharth%20Luthra%20appeared%20for%20Siddaramaiah%20and%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Singhvi%2C%20the%20criminal%20case%20was%20registered%20for%20exercising%20the%20right%20to%20protest%20and%20is%20totally%20against%20the%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20expression%20under%20Article%2019%20(1)%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20this%2C%20Justice%20Mishra%20responded%20by%20saying%20that%20the%20offences%20which%20have%20been%20invoked%20in%20the%20case%20have%20been%20kept%20in%20the%20statute%20books%20keeping%20in%20view%20the%20reasonable%20restrictions%20under%20the%20fundamental%20rights.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%80%9CElse%20whatever%20disturbances%20are%20there%20on%20roads%2C%20we%20have%20to%20quash.%20Your%20argument%20is%20%E2%80%A6%20politicians%20do%20it%2C%20it%20has%20to%20be%20quashed%3F%E2%80%9D%20Mishra%20retorted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20then%20went%20on%20to%20ask%20if%20permission%20had%20been%20sought%20for%20the%20demonstration.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20cannot%20go%20one%20fine%20morning%20and%20assemble%20in%20thousands%2C%20and%20%5Bthen%5D%20says%20nothing%20can%20happen%20to%20us%20because%20we%20are%20protesting%E2%80%A6%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20Sibal%20said%20that%20law%20and%20order%20cannot%20be%20a%20ground%20to%20deny%20a%20fundamental%20right.%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20a%20constitutional%20right%2C%20a%20fundamental%20right%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sibal%20added%2C%20on%20behalf%20of%20petitioners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Siddarmaiah%E2%80%99s%20petition%2C%20in%20the%20instant%20case%2C%20none%20of%20the%20offences%20mentioned%20in%20Section%20141%20(unlawful%20assembly)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20are%20met.%20It%20also%20added%20that%20no%20violence%20stemmed%20out%20of%20the%20assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708343977000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F18164526%2FFwBN2HcakAEGvBw.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-stays-proceedings-against-siddaramaiah-others-in-the-2022-protest-march-case%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%202022%20case%20pertains%20to%20protest%20march%20held%20by%20Congress%20leaders%20demanding%20the%20resignation%20of%20K.S.%20Eshwarappa%2C%20th