ml%5C%22%3E%20Independent%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%C2%A0The%20government%20said%20the%20move%20was%20part%20of%20a%20plan%20to%20''minimise%20disruption%20and%20improve%20behaviour%20in%20classrooms.''%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20the%20Education%20Secretary%2C%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BSchools%20are%20places%20for%20children%20to%20learn%20and%20mobile%20phones%20are%2C%20at%20a%20minimum%2C%20an%20unwanted%20distraction%20in%20the%20classroom.%20We%20are%20giving%20our%20hard-working%20teachers%20the%20tools%20to%20take%20action%20to%20help%20improve%20behaviour%20and%20to%20allow%20them%20to%20do%20what%20they%20do%20best%2C%20teach.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20for%20Education%20has%20published%20guidance%20to%20ensure%20all%20classrooms%20across%20England%20follow%20the%20same%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20determined%20that%20all%20schools%20should%20prohibit%20the%20use%20of%20mobile%20phones%20throughout%20the%20school%20day%E2%80%94not%20only%20during%20lessons%20but%20during%20breaks%20and%20lunchtimes%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20guidance%20read.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20guidance%20warned%20that%2C%20in%20some%20schools%2C%20the%20use%20of%20mobile%20phones%20remains%20a%20''daily%20battle.''%C2%A0The%20document%20suggested%20four%20different%20scenarios%20for%20implementing%20the%20ban.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20includes%20a%20total%20ban%20that%20requires%20students%20to%20leave%20their%20devices%20at%20home%2C%20the%20second%20requires%20them%20to%20turn%20them%20in%20to%20school%20staff%20upon%20arrival.%20The%20third%20includes%20an%20option%20that%20requires%20them%20to%20keep%20the%20phones%20in%20secure%20storage%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bnever%20used%2C%20seen%2C%20or%20heard%26quot%3B.%20The%20last%20option%20allows%20students%20to%20keep%20their%20devices%20within%20easy%20reach%20under%20the%20condition%20that%20they%20never%20use%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStudents%20who%20violate%20the%20new%20rules%20will%20receive%20detention%20or%20face%20phone%20confiscation%2C%20the%20guidance%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20believes%20that%20removing%20mobile%20phones%20can%20help%20children%20and%20young%20people%20spend%20more%20time%20being%20active%20and%20socialising%20face-to-face%20with%20their%20peers%2C%20which%20will%20help%20their%20mental%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it's%20currently%20up%20to%20individual%20school%20headteachers%20in%20England%20to%20decide%20their%20policies%20on%20mobile%20phones%20in%20schools.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEducation%20Secretary%20Gillian%20Keegan%20said%20it%20would%20provide%20''clarity%20and%20consistency''%20for%20teachers%20and%20that%20there%20is%20currently%20''a%20large%20variation%20in%20how%20different%20schools%20are%20managing%20the%20use%20of%20mobile%20phones.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20added%2C%20''Schools%20are%20places%20for%20children%20to%20learn%20and%20mobile%20phones%20are%2C%20at%20a%20minimum%2C%20an%20unwanted%20distraction%20in%20the%20classroom.%20We%20are%20giving%20our%20hard-working%20teachers%20the%20tools%20to%20take%20action%20to%20help%20improve%20behaviour%20and%20to%20allow%20them%20to%20do%20what%20they%20do%20best%20%E2%80%93%20teach.''%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708341240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2F2l9avao8_mobile-phones-in-schools_625x300_19_February_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fthis-country-is-planning-a-complete-ban-on-mobile-phones-in-schools-5087053%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22However%2C%20it's%20currently%20up%20to%20individual%20school%20headteachers%20in%20England%20to%20decide%20their%20policies%20on%20mobile%20phones%20in%20schools.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fthis-country-is-planning-a-complete-ban-on-mobile-phones-in-schools-5087053%22%2C%2