ower%20generating%20company%20Rajasthan%20Rajya%20Vidyut%20Utpadan%20Nigam%2C%20the%20Adani%20Group%20was%20awarded%20the%20contract%20as%20%E2%80%98mine%20developer%20and%20operator%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20tree%20felling%20occurred%20with%20the%20support%20of%20a%20massive%20police%20force%20and%20Adivasi%20villagers%20were%20detained%20for%20the%20day.%20Protests%20erupted%20and%20on%20January%207%2C%202024%2C%20barricades%20were%20erected%20in%20Raipur%2C%20Bilaspur%20and%20elsewhere%20to%20prevent%20hundreds%20from%20participating%20in%20the%20rallies.%20Nonetheless%20support%20has%20been%20pouring%20in%20well%20beyond%20the%20local%20level.%20The%20cry%20of%20%E2%80%9CHasdeo%20Bachao%E2%80%9D%20has%20found%20resonance%20in%20neighbouring%20Bastar%2C%20and%20has%20transcended%20state%20boundaries%2C%20finding%20echoes%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20too.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlok%20Shukla%2C%20one%20of%20the%20founding%20members%20of%20the%20struggle%20and%20convenor%20of%20the%20Chhattisgarh%20Bachao%20Andolan%2C%20an%20umbrella%20body%20for%20movements%20across%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20points%20out%20how%20despite%20repression%2C%20the%20movement%20has%20garnered%20solidarity%20from%20a%20vast%20cross%20section%20of%20society.%20These%20include%20farmers%E2%80%99%20organisations%2C%20mine%20workers%2C%20environmentalists%2C%20and%20movements%20against%20iron%20ore%20mining%2C%20among%20others.%20It%20attracted%20the%20urban-centric%20population%20of%20Chhattisgarh.%20Shukla%20spoke%20of%20doctors%20trying%20to%20cross%20the%20barricade%20at%20Raipur%20during%20the%20protest.%20As%20a%20mark%20of%20how%20widespread%20the%20protest%20has%20been%2C%20he%20also%20highlighted%20the%20situation%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Egau%20rakshak%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20or%20cow%20protector%20who%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20subscribe%20to%20the%20politics%20of%20Hindutva%20but%20is%20concerned%20that%20cattle%20will%20suffer%20if%20the%20forest%20disappears.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20404px)%2085vw%2C%20404px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19151759%2FAlok-Shukla-convenor-Chhattisgar-938x1024.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22404%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19151759%2FAlok-Shukla-convenor-Chhattisgar-938x1024.jpg%20938w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19151759%2FAlok-Shukla-convenor-Chhattisgar-275x300.jpg%20275w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19151759%2FAlok-Shukla-convenor-Chhattisgar.jpg%201099w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697803%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22441%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAlok%20Shukla%20is%20one%20of%20the%20founding%20members%20of%20the%20struggle.%20Photo%3A%20Freny%20Manecksha%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESuch%20widespread%20support%2C%20Shukla%20said%2C%20comes%20because%20of%20the%20powerful%20Adivasi%20articulation%20of%20beliefs%20and%20culture%20which%20resonates%20with%20wider%20issues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20not%20about%20trees%20being%20cut%20in%20one%20particular%20village%20or%20about%20opposing%20one%20project.%20Emphasis%20is%20on%20the%20forest%20as%20a%20whole%2C%20whereby%20felling%20of%20trees%20or%20the%20dying%20river%20reflects%20destruction%20of%20a%20rich%20ecosystem%20and%20crucial%20wider%20environmental%20impact.%20Climate%20change%20and%20the%20survival%20of%20the%20planet%20%E2%80%93%20these%20are%20issues%20the%20whole%20world%20is%20talking%20about%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStretching%20across%20170%2C000%20hectares%2C%20the%20Hasdeo-Arand%20is%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20most%20pristine%20and%20contiguous%20tracts%20of%20forest.%20It%20houses%20Gond%20Adivasis%20and%20is%20home%20to%20several%20plant%20and%20animal%20species%2C%20many%20of%20which%20are%20endangered.%20It%20is%20the%20catchment%20area%20for%20the%20perennial%20Hasdeo%20river%20that%20flows%20into%20the%20Mahanadi%20and%20provides%20water%20to%20the%20Surguja%20district.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20forest%20contains%20a%20coalfield%20of%20over%20a%20billion%20metric%20tonnes%20of%20coal%20located%20close%20to%20the%20surface%20and%20easy%20to%20mine.%20These%20coal%20blocks%20have%20become%20the%20flash%20point%20despite%20it%20once%20having%20been%20declared%20a%20%E2%80%98no-go%E2%80%99%20zone%20by%20the%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPolitical%20party%20lines%20have%20blurred%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20taking%20a%20stand%20on%20the%20mining%20and%20tree%20felling.%20Both%20the%20Congress%20and%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20trade%20charges%20over%20which%20government%20first%20allowed%20it.%20Shukla%20points%20out%20that%20what%20is%20remarkable%2C%20though%2C%20is%20how%20it%20was%20the%20movement%E2%80%99s%20dogged%20determination%20which%20brought%20about%20the%20unanimous%20resolution%20passed%20on%20July%2026%2C%202022%2C%20in%20the%20assembly.%20Both%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Congress%20which%20was%20then%20in%20power%2C%20asked%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20ensure%20that%20no%20mining%20activities%20would%20be%20carried%20out%20in%20Hasdeo.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20significant%2C%20he%20adds%2C%20how%20Adivasis%20up%20against%20powerful%20forces%20have%20been%20able%20to%20counter%20arguments%20on%20development%20and%20put%20out%20their%20own%20narratives%20based%20on%20their%20vision%20and%20ethics.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fhasdeo-arand-deforestation-raises-questions-of-adivasi-justice-for-chhattisgarhs-first-tribal-cm%5C%22%3EHasdeo%20Arand%20Deforestation%20Raises%20Questions%20of%20Adivasi%20Justice%20for%20Chhattisgarh%E2%80%99s%20First%20Tribal%20CM%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20Arunopol%20Seal%2C%20a%20senior%20development%20consultant%20on%20desirable%20change%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sahapedia.org%2Fout-forest-products-people-and-their-markets-uttar-bastar-0%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%3Cem%3ESahapedia%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Adivasis%20have%20a%20symbiotic%20relationship%20with%20the%20forest%2C%20and%20see%20it%20as%20a%20living%20being.%20Forests%20provide%20livelihood%20and%20sustenance.%20Adivasis%20have%20so%20far%20kept%20away%20from%20seeing%20them%20as%20circuits%20of%20capital.%20They%20envisage%20themselves%20as%20guardians%20protecting%20the%20environment.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EExemplifying%20this%20holistic%20view%20of%20the%20forest%2C%20Sunita%20Porte%2C%20a%20fiery%20young%20woman%20from%20Fatehpur%20village%2C%20spoke%20to%20me%20of%20how%20the%20rivulet%20that%20flows%20across%20their%20region%20feeds%20the%20Hasdeo%20river.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20water%20all%20year%20round.%20Our%20opposition%20to%20mining%20protects%20this%20river%20that%20provides%20water%20for%20the%20farmers.%20Korba%2C%20with%20its%20numerous%20power%20plants%2C%20is%20dependent%20on%20that%20plentiful%20water.%20What%20will%20happen%20if%20the%20river%20dries%20up%20with%20tree%20felling%20and%20mining%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESignificantly%2C%20farmers%20of%20the%20region%20were%20among%20those%20who%20attempted%20to%20take%20out%20a%20rally%20in%20support%20on%20January%207.%20At%20the%20national%20level%2C%20Bhartiya%20Kisan%20Sangh%20leader%20Rakesh%20Tikait%20spoke%20out%20strongly%20and%20vowed%20support%20for%20the%20struggle.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FJecyV4qgbj0%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Hasdeo%20Movement%20%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%82%20BKU%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%80%20%E0%A4%8F%E0%A4%82%E0%A4%9F%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%80%2C%20Rakesh%20Tikait%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%BE%20BJP%20%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B0%20%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%B0%20%E0%A4%AC%E0%A4%A1%E0%A4%BC%E0%A4%BE%20%E0%A4%86%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8B%E0%A4%AA%20%7C%20Chhattisgarh%20News%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22473%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESunita%20also%20voiced%20concern%20for%20wildlife%2C%20and%20for%20the%20man-animal%20conflict.%20In%20typical%20Adivasi%20narration%2C%20akin%20to%20that%20of%20a%20fable%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20not%20only%20us%20whose%20homes%20will%20be%20uprooted%20if%20the%20mining%20continues%20but%20wildlife%20too.%20Where%20will%20the%20birds%20and%20others%20go%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20spoke%20of%20a%20small%20herd%20of%20elephants%20coming%20out%20of%20the%20forest%2C%20of%20a%20lone%20elephant%20separated%20from%20the%20herd%2C%20roaming%20close%20to%20people%E2%80%99s%20homes%20after%20the%20trees%20were%20cut.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20heard%20they%20damaged%20some%20houses.%20People%20say%20the%20houses%20were%20those%20of%20agents%20of%20the%20company.%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%98Company%E2%80%99%20is%20the%20word%20commonly%20used%20for%20the%20Adani%20Group%20in%20these%20areas.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20anecdote%20%E2%80%93%20that%20of%20a%20bear%20giving%20birth%20to%20cubs%20near%20someone%E2%80%99s%20home%20because%20it%20had%20to%20flee%20the%20forest%20%E2%80%93%20was%20narrated%20not%20just%20by%20Sunita%20but%20has%20become%20something%20of%20folklore%2C%20gaining%20currency%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20Twitter%2C%20to%20bolster%20the%20meta-narrative%20of%20displacement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20concern%20for%20this%20wildlife%20which%20spurred%20Adivasi%20youth%20Yogesh%20Markam%20to%20cycle%20across%20neighbouring%20Bastar%20district%20to%20raise%20awareness%20of%20Hasdeo%2C%20as%20his%20act%20of%20solidarity.%20A%20local%20daily%20featured%20his%20journey.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19150545%2F1707473670874-1-e1708335747564-837x1024.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22837%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19150545%2F1707473670874-1-e1708335747564-837x1024.jpg%20837w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19150545%2F1707473670874-1-e1708335747564-245x300.jpg%20245w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19150545%2F1707473670874-1-e1708335747564.jpg%20927w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697794%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20local%20daily%20in%20Bastar%20carried%20a%20photograph%20of%20Adivasi%20youth%20Yogesh%20Markam%20who%20was%20on%20a%20cycle%20trip%20rallying%20support%20for%20the%20Hasdeo%20struggle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESuch%20smaller%20stories%20are%20indicative%20of%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20movement%20is%20spurring%20Adivasi%20youth%20to%20tell%20their%20own%20stories%2C%20in%20their%20individualistic%20ways.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20are%20leading%20the%20campaigns%20in%20social%20media.%20It%20is%20their%20voices%20that%20are%20being%20amplified%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Shukla.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJacinta%20Kerketta%2C%20acclaimed%20Adivasi%20poet%20and%20activist%2C%20arrived%20at%20the%20dharna%20site%20where%20protesters%20have%20been%20sitting%20in%2C%20in%20a%20relay%2C%20for%20over%20700%20days%2C%20to%20show%20her%20support.%20Since%20her%20visit%2C%20she%20has%20posted%20on%20social%20media%20as%20well.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22hi%5C%22%3E%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%87%20%E0%A4%9C%E0%A5%80%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%A8%20%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%BE%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E0%A4%94%E0%A4%B0%20%E0%A4%AC%E0%A4%A6%E0%A4%B2%E0%A5%87%20%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%97%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A8%20%E0%A4%A6%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%BE.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FSaveHasdeoForest%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23SaveHasdeoForest%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cbr%3E%5CnPC%20%3A%20Kranti.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Fz4U4yKy4pT%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2Fz4U4yKy4pT%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Jacinta%20Kerketta%20(%40JacintaKerkett2)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FJacintaKerkett2%2Fstatus%2F1749717537171149253%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJanuary%2023%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%3EIn%20Kanker%2C%20North%20Bastar%2C%20Rubjee%20Salaam%2C%20an%20Adivasi%20law%20student%2C%20took%20time%20out%20between%20studying%20for%20his%20impending%20exams%20to%20lead%20a%20small%20rally%20and%20hand%20a%20memorandum%20to%20the%20Collector.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDisputing%20the%20popular%20notions%20of%C2%A0%20development%2C%20he%20told%20me%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhy%20are%20Adivasis%20who%20lived%20in%20isolation%20and%20without%20any%20government%20intervention%2C%20coming%20out%20on%20the%20streets%3F%20Why%20do%20we%20oppose%20road%20building%3F%20It%20is%20because%20we%20know%20it%20is%20land%20acquisition%20for%20mining%20that%20is%20at%20the%20core%2C%20not%20%3Cem%3Evikas%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5Bdevelopment%5D%20or%20any%20%3Cem%3Eyojana%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5Bpublic%20scheme%5D%20agenda.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHasdeo%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20a%20fight%20for%20all%20of%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20for%20central%20India%20and%20the%20nation.%20%E2%80%9CSaving%20it%20is%20our%20collective%20responsibility.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDual%20strategy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20notable%20feature%20of%20the%20Hasdeo%20movement%20is%20the%20way%20it%20has%20adopted%20a%20dual%20strategy.%20Beside%20civil%20disobedience%20through%20protests%2C%20rallies%2C%20padayatras%2C%20and%20dharnas%20it%20has%20sought%20to%20challenge%20the%20state%20and%20the%20Adani%20Group%20through%20the%20assertion%20of%20rights%20and%20guarantees%20for%20Adivasis%20under%20the%20constitution.%20It%20is%20also%20a%20struggle%20where%20women%20have%20been%20very%20forceful%20and%20displayed%20their%20capabilities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPrasaddobai%20Porte%2C%20in%20her%20sixties%2C%20whose%20son%20Jainandan%20Porte%20is%20the%20sarpanch%20of%C2%A0%20Ghatbharra%2C%20one%20of%20the%20project-affected%20villages%2C%20spoke%20in%20Chhattisgarhi%20of%20this%20legal%20route.%20She%20traced%20the%20journey%20from%20days%20of%20a%20determined%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENi%20chhaiyet%2C%20ni%20diyat%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(Don%E2%80%99t%20want%20compensation%2C%20won%E2%80%99t%20give%20land)%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20assertion%20of%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EHamri%20jameen%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Et%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehe%20forest%20is%20our%20land).%E2%80%9D%20It%20is%20an%20example%20of%20how%20simple%20determination%20was%20later%20buttressed%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Einformation%20and%20political%20consciousness.%20This%20includes%20being%20familiar%20with%20the%20Forest%20Rights%20Act%20and%20the%20Panchayats%20Extension%20to%20Scheduled%20Area%20(PESA)%20Act%20which%20gives%20some%20degree%20of%20self-governance%20to%20people%20in%20certain%20areas.%20Gram%20Sabhas%20or%20village%20councils%20need%20to%20give%20written%20consent%20for%20mining%20or%20any%20other%20project%20to%20be%20undertaken.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELegal%20activist%20Shalini%20Gera%20explains%20how%20an%20attempt%20to%20deploy%20the%20Forest%20Rights%20Act%2C%20a%20landmark%20legislation%2C%20was%20made.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CPeople%20have%20been%20living%20in%20forests%20for%20years%20and%20because%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ejhum%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20cultivation%20they%20sometimes%20moved%20from%20one%20area%20to%20another%20but%20there%20was%20no%20question%20of%20pattas%20or%20formal%20titles.%20In%20the%201900s%20the%20British%20brought%20the%20notion%20that%20forests%20belonged%20to%20the%20sovereign%2C%20nationalizing%20it%20so%20to%20speak%2C%20and%20prohibiting%20shifting%20agriculture%20and%20collection%20of%20forest%20produce.%20People%20who%20lived%20in%20forests%20were%20seen%20as%20encroachers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20continued%20after%20independence.%20Adivasis%E2%80%99%20activities%20were%20seen%20as%20criminal%20even%20though%20their%20lives%20revolved%20around%20the%20forest.%20They%20were%20at%20the%20mercy%20of%20the%20forest%20department.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202006%20the%20Forest%20Rights%20Act%20was%20passed.%20It%2C%20said%20Gera%2C%20acknowledged%20that%20%E2%80%9Cforest%20dwellers%E2%80%9D%20who%20had%20access%20to%20the%20forests%20till%20December%202005%20already%20possessed%20the%20rights%20to%20the%20forests.%20Authorities%20created%20in%20the%20Act%20would%20record%20these%20rights%20that%20already%20existed.%20It%20was%20also%20path-breaking%20legislation%2C%20she%20adds%2C%20because%20of%20the%20concept%20of%20community%20rights.%20People%20could%20stake%20claim%20on%20the%20forest%20that%20they%20had%20been%20accessing%20till%20the%20cut-off%20date.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Act%20was%20notified%20in%20January%202008%20and%20whilst%20people%20were%20familiar%20with%20individual%20rights%20it%20was%20only%20around%202013%20onwards%2C%20said%20Gera%2C%20that%20community%20forest%20rights%20came%20to%20be%20understood%20and%20claims%20made.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CGhatbarra%20in%20Hasdeo%20forest%2C%20slated%20for%20mining%2C%20was%20probably%20the%20first%20village%20in%20Chhattisgarh%20to%20make%20the%20claim%20of%20community%20forest%20resource%20rights%20(CFRR).%20The%20CFRR%20title%2C%20giving%20the%20Gram%20Sabha%20the%20right%20to%20manage%20the%20forest%20within%20its%20traditional%20boundary%2C%20was%20given%20in%20September%202013.%20Villagers%20opposed%20to%20the%20mining%20were%20now%20asserting%20to%20the%20Adani%20firm%20when%20it%20came%20to%20do%20surveys%20that%20the%20forest%20land%20belonged%20to%20them%20and%20not%20the%20company.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19150749%2F1707473670881-mine-1-e1708335723871-1024x612.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19150749%2F1707473670881-mine-1-e1708335723871-1024x612.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19150749%2F1707473670881-mine-1-e1708335723871-300x179.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19150749%2F1707473670881-mine-1-e1708335723871.jpg%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697796%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22502%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20mining%20site%20which%20has%20ravaged%20the%20land.%20Efforts%20to%20begin%20phase%20two%20are%20on%20with%20the%20latest%20round%20of%20tree%20felling%20by%20the%20newly%20elected%20BJP%20government%20despite%20a%20joint%20resolution%20in%20the%20assembly%20on%20July%2026%2C%202022%2C%20asking%20the%20Centre%20to%20desist%20from%20mining.%20Photo%3A%20Freny%20Manecksha%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20January%208%2C%202016%2C%20the%20village%20received%20a%20notice%20from%20the%20district%20collector%2C%20divisional%20forest%20officer%20and%20assistant%20commissioner%20of%20tribal%20development%20that%20their%20CFRR%20had%20been%20cancelled.%20The%20Adani%20Group%20had%20complained%20that%20they%20received%20forest%20clearance%20for%20mining%20before%20the%20villagers%20staked%20their%20claim.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELegal%20experts%20in%20forest%20rights%20opine%20that%20the%20law%20is%20very%20clear%20that%20the%20rights%20are%20vested%20in%20the%20people%20from%20the%20very%20day%20the%20Act%20came%20into%20being%20and%20not%20when%20they%20received%20the%20title.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20has%20also%20been%20argued%20the%20district%20collector%20did%20not%20bother%20to%20check%20or%20clarify%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20pretext%20of%20having%20received%20forest%20clearance.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20fact%2C%20forest%20clearance%20had%20been%20set%20aside%20by%20the%20National%20Green%20Tribunal%20(NGT)%20in%202014%20and%20whilst%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20its%20partial%20stay%20of%20the%20NGT%20order%20allowed%20mining%2C%20it%20did%20not%20stay%20the%20part%20related%20to%20forest%20clearance.%20Gera%2C%20who%20is%20representing%20the%20villagers%20in%20the%20case%20in%20the%20high%20court%20says%20this%20leaves%20one%20in%20a%20very%20grey%20zone%2C%20where%20mining%20is%20allowed%20despite%20there%20being%20no%20valid%20forest%20clearance%20order.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20matter%20of%20community%20forest%20rights%20has%20been%20in%20the%20high%20court%20since%202016%20but%20no%20finding%20has%20yet%20been%20recorded.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDuping%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20other%20charge%20by%20the%20villagers%20increasingly%20being%20reiterated%20is%20that%20of%20fake%20Gram%20Sabha%20proceedings.%20Villagers%20have%20charged%20that%20the%20mandatory%20written%20assents%20under%20PESA%20for%20Hariharpur%2C%20Salhi%20and%20Fatehpur%20are%20fake.%20Ghatbharra%20in%202011%2C%20and%20again%20in%202021%2C%20had%20passed%20a%20resolution%20in%20its%20Gram%20Sabha%20proceedings%20opposing%20mining.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202018%20when%20people%20came%20to%20learn%20that%20fake%20signatures%20had%20been%20collected%2C%20complaints%20were%20filed%20in%20the%20police%20station%20and%20also%20with%20the%20collector%20but%20no%20action%20was%20taken.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20October%202021%2C%20hundreds%20of%20villagers%20from%20Hasdeo%20made%20a%20300-km%20foot%20march%20over%2010%20days%20to%20Raipur%20to%20demand%20a%20probe%20into%20the%20way%20land%20acquisition%20and%20forest%20clearances%20went%20ahead%20despite%20their%20complaints%20of%20false%20dealings%20and%20fake%20Gram%20Sabha%20proceedings.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20met%20Bhupesh%20Baghel%2C%20then%20chief%20minister%2C%20and%20Governor%20Anusuiya%20Uikey%20who%20assured%20them%20a%20probe%20would%20be%20ordered.%20But%20nothing%20was%20done.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESays%20Sunita%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20met%20whoever%20we%20could%20from%20the%20administration.%20Collector%2C%20tehsildar.%20We%20have%20knocked%20on%20every%20possible%20door%20of%20justice.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20hear%20us%20out%20silently%20and%20do%20nothing.%20We%20met%20T.S.%20Singh%20Deo%20%5Bformer%20minister%20of%20energy%20and%20later%20deputy%20CM%20in%20the%20Congress-led%20government%5D%20who%20assured%20us%20there%20would%20be%20no%20more%20tree%20felling.%20But%20then%20the%20BJP%20formed%20the%20government%20and%20just%20days%20later%2C%20it%20has%20begun.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19151502%2F1148-Nandai-Kumari-Porte-e1708335971393-995x1024.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19151502%2F1148-Nandai-Kumari-Porte-e1708335971393-995x1024.jpg%20995w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19151502%2F1148-Nandai-Kumari-Porte-e1708335971393-291x300.jpg%20291w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19151502%2F1148-Nandai-Kumari-Porte-e1708335971393.jpg%201116w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697802%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22864%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENandai%20Kumari%20Portai%20is%20a%20feisty%20member%20of%20the%20movement%20from%20its%20earliest%20days.%20Photo%3A%20Freny%20Manecksha%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlso%20participating%20in%20the%20padayatra%20of%202021%20was%20Nandai%20Kumari%20Porte%20of%20Ghatbarra%2C%20a%20feisty%20old%20lady%2C%20possibly%20in%20her%20late%20sixties.%20She%20was%20eager%20to%20share%20her%20vibrant%20memories%20of%20the%20struggle.%20Whilst%20she%20was%20fuzzy%20on%20exact%20dates%20she%20did%20convey%20vividly%20the%20emotions%20and%20anecdotes%20of%20a%20people%20in%20protest.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20remember%20when%20the%20Company%20first%20arrived%20in%20the%20village.%20The%20administration%20set%20up%20a%20tent%2C%20gave%20us%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Echai%20biskoot%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20which%20we%20refused%20and%20tried%20to%20talk%20to%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20credits%20the%20late%20Hira%20Singh%20Markam%2C%20Adivasi%20leader%20of%20the%20Gondwana%20Gantantra%20Party%2C%20with%20arousing%20political%20consciousness%20and%20educating%20them%20on%20the%20effects%20of%20mining%20and%20the%20market%20value%20of%20their%20lands.%20Thereafter%20she%20helped%20mobilize%20others%20and%20attended%20many%20rallies%20affirming%20they%20would%20not%20give%20up%20their%20land.%20They%20sat%20in%20dharna%20in%20Fatehpur%20and%20again%20at%20Hariharpur.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20says%20when%20they%20met%20former%20chief%20minister%20Baghel%20she%20complained%20about%20how%20hundreds%20of%20their%20trees%20were%20cut.%20In%20unequivocal%20tones%20she%20told%20him%20the%20Company%20had%20to%20go.%20%E2%80%9CCompany%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ebaandhe%20apna%20boriya%20bistar%2C%20loha%20lakkad.%20Chale%20jai%20apna%20des%E2%80%A6Nahi%20jayega%20toh%20kaatenge%20usske%20pahiyae.%20Hum%20hai%20Adivasi%2C%20Maarange%20chhar%20lathi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E(The%20Company%20should%20pack%20up%20all%20its%20belongings%20and%20materials%20and%20go%20back%20to%20its%20own%20lands.%20Otherwise%2C%20we%20will%20cut%20off%20its%20wheels%20and%20wield%20our%20lathis.%20We%20are%20Adivasis!)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20dismisses%20the%20Company%E2%80%99s%20plans%20for%20re%20settlement%20at%20Basan%20in%20the%20small%20one-bedroom%20house%20kitchen%20colony%20that%20has%20been%20constructed.%20%E2%80%9CNobody%20stays%20there%20and%20nobody%20knows%20where%20the%20people%20of%20Kete%20went%20after%20they%20were%20displaced.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20dharna%20site%20just%20a%20short%20distance%20from%20the%20mine%2C%20where%20men%20and%20women%20have%20sat%20in%20relay%20for%20over%20two%20years%2C%20the%20men%20talked%20of%20the%20extreme%20repression%20they%20faced%20on%20December%2021%2C%202022%20before%20the%20tree%20felling%20operations%20began.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19151011%2F1707471313758-Hasdeo-dharna-site-1-e1708335777680-1024x724.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19151011%2F1707471313758-Hasdeo-dharna-site-1-e1708335777680-1024x724.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19151011%2F1707471313758-Hasdeo-dharna-site-1-e1708335777680-300x212.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19151011%2F1707471313758-Hasdeo-dharna-site-1-e1708335777680.jpg%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697798%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22594%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EProtesters%20have%20been%20sitting%20in%20dharna%20at%20a%20particular%20site%20in%20the%20forest%2C%20close%20to%20the%20mining%20area%2C%20for%20over%20700%20days.%20They%20take%20it%20in%20turns%20to%20come%20and%20sit%20and%20it%20is%20the%20venue%20at%20which%20all%20other%20supporters%20and%20media%20persons%20come.%20Photo%3A%20Freny%20Manecksha%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERamlal%20Porte%20narrated%20how%20around%205%20am%2C%20a%20policeman%20in%20uniform%20and%20some%20others%20in%20plainclothes%20forced%20their%20way%20into%20his%20house.%20Holding%20him%20by%20the%20hand%20they%20announced%20he%20was%20being%20taken%20to%20the%20police%20station%20to%20meet%20with%20a%20senior%20officer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20asked%20them%2C%20%E2%80%98W