elations%20with%20Bangladesh%20but%20we%20have%20already%20made%20clear%20our%20desire%20to%20see%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.saperspectives.net%2Fwhite-house-previews-modi-visit-reiterates-stancetowards-bangladesh-elections%2F%5C%22%3EBangladesh%3C%2Fa%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20taken%20out%20of%20context%2C%20the%20statement%20might%20sound%20a%20bit%20off%20the%20road%2C%20however%2C%20the%20US%20has%20been%20consistently%20expressing%20its%20support%20for%20democracy%20in%20Bangladesh.%20In%20fact%2C%20Bangladesh%20was%20made%20%E2%80%98a%20centerpiece%20of%20Biden%20administration%E2%80%99s%20effort%20to%20place%20democracy%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fbangladesh-shows-the-limits-of-bidens-democracy-promotion-81afa9e5%5C%22%3EU.S%20foreign%20policy%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20name%3D%5C%22_ftnref2%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fis-washington-turning-a-new-page-on-bangladesh%23_ftn2%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20%E2%80%98dummy%20election%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20election%2C%20popularly%20dubbed%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98dummy%20election%E2%80%99%2C%20was%20held%20in%20Dhaka%20on%20January%207%2C%202024%2C%20where%20Sheikh%20Hasina%E2%80%99s%20party%20Awami%20League%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20face%20any%20competition.%20The%20election%20sealed%20the%20fate%20of%20Bangladesh%20as%20a%20one%20party-ruled%20autocratic%20state.%20A%20month%20after%20the%20election%2C%20Hasina%E2%80%99s%20top%20civil%20servant%20Masud%20Bin%20Momen%20received%20a%20letter%20from%20President%20Joseph%20R.%20Biden%2C%20intended%20for%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20expressing%20%E2%80%98interest%20to%20work%20with%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99.%20With%20the%20sealed%20letter%2C%20has%20the%20US%20made%20a%20180-degree%20turn%20from%20its%20policy%20of%20%E2%80%98promoting%20democracy%E2%80%99%20in%20Bangladesh%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20plausible%20answer%20to%20that%20is%20a%20yes.%20At%20least%20lack%20of%20any%20tangible%20action%20after%20the%20fraudulent%20election%20is%20forcing%20some%20to%20ponder%20if%20the%20US%20has%20backtracked%20from%20the%20democracy-promotion%20agenda%20in%20Bangladesh.%20The%20White%20House%20letter%20to%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20gives%20serious%20credence%20to%20that%20understanding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20US%20actions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20run%20up%20to%20the%20elections%2C%20there%20have%20been%20a%20series%20of%20statements%20and%20significant%20actions%20from%20the%20US%20in%20which%20the%20need%20for%20a%20free%20and%20credible%20elections%20in%20the%20South%20Asian%20country%20was%20underlined%20in%20the%20last%20two%20a%20half%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20the%20US%20actions%20significantly%20started%20with%20sanctions%20against%20the%20Rapid%20Action%20Battalion%20(RAB)%2C%20the%20notorious%20paramilitary%20forces%2C%C2%A0%20allegedly%20accused%20for%20massive%20human%20rights%20violations%20including%20enforced%20disappearances%2C%20tortures%20and%20killings.%20Long%20before%20the%20elections%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20the%20US%20secretary%20of%20state%20Antony%20Blinken%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Fannouncement-of-visa-policy-to-promote-democratic-elections-in-bangladesh%2F%5C%22%3Edeclared%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20US%20visa%20restrictions%20policy%20for%20Bangladesh%20nationals%20for%20%E2%80%98undermining%20democratic%20election%20process%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20clarify%20the%20US%20visa%20restrictions%2C%20Assistant%20Secretary%20Bureau%20Of%20South%20And%20Central%20Asian%20Affairs%20Donald%20Lu%2C%20appeared%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbd.usembassy.gov%2F29801%2F%5C%22%3ETV%20talk%20show%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Bangladesh%3Cspan%3E.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20State%20Department%20and%20NSC%E2%80%99s%20spokespersons%20have%20repeatedly%20reaffirmed%20the%20US%20position%20on%20holding%20a%20credible%20and%20participatory%20elections%20in%20Bangladesh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20Hasina%E2%80%99s%20ministers%20indicated%20that%20India%20may%20help%20them%20get%20away%20with%20the%20US%20pressure%20for%20a%20democratic%20election.%20Although%20it%20was%20assumed%20that%20Delhi%20would%20convince%20Washington%20not%20to%20be%20involved%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20backyard%2C%20specially%20for%20the%20case%20of%20Bangladesh%2C%20Dhaka%20received%20a%20letter%20from%20Donal%20Lu%2C%20right%20after%20the%20two%20plus%20two%20dialogues%20in%20Delhi%2C%20urging%20the%20political%20parties%20to%20arrange%20dialogues%20for%20a%20participatory%20election.%20That%20letter%20made%20it%20plausible%20that%20the%20ball%20was%20on%20Sheikh%20Hasina%E2%80%99s%20court%20to%20initiate%C2%A0%20processes%20for%20free%20and%20fair%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20the%20letter%2C%20with%20an%20already%20put%20in%20place%20%E2%80%983C%E2%80%99%20visa%20restrictions%20indicated%20Dhaka%20might%20face%20the%20US%20dissatisfaction%20if%20they%20denied%20holding%20free%20elections%20as%20understood%20by%20many.%20After%20all%20these%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98dummy%20election%E2%80%99%20has%20ended%20and%20now%20Hasina%2C%20being%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20has%20received%20letter%20of%20%E2%80%98interest%20to%20work%20together%E2%80%99%20from%20President%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20no%20US%20action%2C%20visibly%2C%20against%20Hasina%E2%80%99s%20government%20for%20%E2%80%98undermining%20democratic%20elections%E2%80%99%20which%20certainly%20didn%E2%80%99t%20reflect%20the%20will%20of%20the%20people.%20Foreign%20policy%20expert%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.prothomalo.com%2Fopinion%2Finterview%2Fipfigtsy2a%5C%22%3E%20Sreeradha%20Datta%3C%2Fa%3E%20observed%20roughly%20ten%20percent%20of%20people%20showed%20up%20for%20the%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20important%20question%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20the%20US%20created%20enough%20buzz%20for%20holding%20a%20free%20election%20and%20didn%E2%80%99t%20take%20any%20action%20after%20the%20polls%2C%20it%20%3C%2Fspan%3Ehas%20created%20a%20murmur%20among%20the%20common%20readers%20and%20experienced%20political%20analysts%20%E2%80%93%20has%20the%20US%20shifted%20the%20%E2%80%98promoting%20democracy%E2%80%99%20policy%20being%20influenced%20by%20India%20as%20Hasina%20is%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20darling%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20get%20a%20clearer%20view%20of%20such%20a%20genuine%20question%2C%20the%20readers%20might%20need%20to%20wait%20a%20few%20more%20months%2C%20for%20certain%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20oxygen%20of%20policy%20time%20in%20Washington%2C%20nowadays%2C%20is%20being%20eaten%20up%20by%20the%20events%20in%20the%20middle%20east.%20Secondly%2C%20even%20if%20the%20US%20wants%20to%20go%20for%20anything%20that%20may%20seem%20to%20be%20punishing%20the%20Hasina%20government%20for%20undermining%20democracy%20and%20the%20US%20national%20security%20interests%20in%20the%20region%2C%20Washington%20needs%20to%20reassess%20the%20situation%20with%20fresh%20perspectives.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20US%20and%20all%20its%20major%20allies%20have%20refrained%20from%20congratulating%20Hasina%E2%80%99s%20questionable%20coronation.%20The%20same%20podiums%20of%20the%20State%20Department%20and%20White%20House%20briefings%20resonate%20with%20the%20same%20message%2C%20a%20call%20for%20restoring%20the%20democratic%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%205%2C%20principal%20deputy%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20State%20Vedant%20Patel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbonikbarta.net%2Fhome%2Fnews_description%2F371873%2FUS-says-visa-restriction-policy-for-undermining-democracy-still-exists%5C%22%3Eresponding%20to%20a%20question%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20%E2%80%983C%E2%80%99%20visa%20restrictions%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThese%20policies%20don%E2%80%99t%20sunset%2C%20just%20because%20the%20election%20is%20over.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20fresh%20assessment%20is%20needed%20about%20who%20is%20holding%20the%20winning%20ground%20in%20Dhaka%20among%20India%2C%20China%20and%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apparent%20US%20inaction%20in%20Bangladesh%20could%20be%20read%20as%20%E2%80%98low%20energy%20extension%20period%E2%80%99%20as%20high%20energy%20is%20put%20for%20the%20middle%20east%20as%20well%20as%20to%20be%20extended%20for%20elections%20slated%20in%20the%20country%20in%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20problem%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20Washington%20not%20being%20able%20to%20put%20much%20policy%20time%20towards%20South%20Asia%2C%20it%20might%20be%20difficult%20to%20take%20off%20the%20paddle%20of%20the%20boat%20due%20to%20strategic%20priorities.%20The%20resumption%20of%20key%20Kyaukphyu%20Indian%20Ocean%20port%2C%20in%20the%20western%20state%20of%20Rakhine%20will%20give%20China%20competitive%20advantage.%20China%20has%2070%20per%20cent%20stake%20in%20the%20port%2C%20literally%20owning%20the%20real%20estate.%20Not%20too%20far%20away%2C%20the%20BNS%C2%A0Sheikh%C2%A0Hasina%20(a%20new%20naval%20base%20that%20has%20been%20developed%20for%20the%20Bangladesh%20Navy)%2C%20operated%20by%20China%2C%20is%20to%20offer%20%E2%80%98secure%20jetty%20facilities%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbgabd.org%2F2023%2F03%2F24%2Fbangladeshs-first-submarine-base-a-step-towards-maritime-capacity-building%2F%5C%22%3Esubmarines%20and%20warships%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20of%20more%20strategic%20importance%20for%20China%2C%20India%20and%20the%20US%2C%20certainly%20not%20for%20Dhaka.%20However%2C%20lack%20of%20democracy%20in%20the%20country%20has%20brought%20an%20unexpected%20discomfort%20for%20Washington%E2%80%99s%20most%20trusted%20partner%20in%20South%20Asia.%20As%20Hasina%E2%80%99s%20opposition%20parties%20are%20introspecting%20for%20the%20next%20courses%20of%20action%20while%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20activists%20and%20leaders%20are%20in%20jail%2C%20some%20barely%20known%20social%20media%20characters%20have%20called%20for%20a%20boycott%20of%20India%2C%20copying%20the%20%E2%80%98India%20Out%E2%80%99%20campaign%20which%20happened%20in%20Maldives.%20It%20is%20too%20early%20to%20assess%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20boycott%2C%20yet%20it%20has%20reached%20a%20level%20that%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20has%20faced%20questions%20if%20India%E2%80%99s%20neighbourhood%20policies%20are%20failing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20Delhi%20not%20sending%20its%20foreign%20secretary%20this%20time%20to%20Dhaka%2C%20as%20was%20done%20in%202014%20to%20ensure%20Hasina%E2%80%99s%20victory%2C%20Indian%20influence%20was%20clearly%20evident.%20The%20common%20sentiment%20towards%20India%20among%20the%20people%20is%20not%20favourable%20for%20the%20neighbouring%20country.%20Regardless%20of%20the%20significant%20backsliding%20of%20democracy%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20attributing%20India%20as%20the%20enabler%20of%20that%20decline%20is%20certainly%20not%20a%20public%20relations%20boost.%20Thus%2C%20Delhi%20will%20have%20to%20face%20the%20consequences%20for%20the%20action%20or%20inaction%20of%20the%20US%20or%20China%20in%20Dhaka.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EMushfiqul%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Fazal%20Ansarey%20is%20working%20as%20the%20State%20Department%20and%20White%20House%20Correspondent%20for%20Just%20News%20BD%20and%20South%20Asia%20Perspectives.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20name%3D%5C%22_ftn4%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fis-washington-turning-a-new-page-on-bangladesh%23_ftnref4%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20name%3D%5C%22_ftn6%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fis-washington-turning-a-new-page-on-bangladesh%23_ftnref6%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708329433000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3