5204%2Fpexels-photo-14907311.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20reason%20for%20political%20contributions%20by%20companies%20is%20as%20open%20as%20daylight.%20Even%20the%20learned%20Solicitor%20General%20did%20not%20deny%20during%20the%20course%20of%20the%20hearings%20that%20corporate%20donations%20are%20made%20to%20receive%20favors%20through%20quid%20pro%20quo%20arrangements.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%88%BC%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20on%20electoral%20bonds%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20did%20not%20mince%20words%20as%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-electoral-bonds-quash-anonymous%5C%22%3Eunequivocally%20declared%3C%2Fa%3E%20anonymous%20electoral%20bonds%20to%20be%20illegal%20and%20unconstitutional.%20The%20element%20of%20%E2%80%9Cquid%20pro%20quo%E2%80%9D%2C%20embedded%20in%20the%20unlimited%20and%20anonymous%20donations%20by%20companies%2C%20can%20play%20out%20in%20several%20insidious%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20one%20self-evident%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20%E2%80%9Cquid%20pro%20quo%E2%80%9D%20might%20have%20worked%20after%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20was%20launched%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20many%20gifts%20to%20big%20business%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20be%20recalled%20that%20the%20scheme%20was%20launched%20mid%202017%2C%20just%20after%20the%20economy%20was%20delivered%20the%20twin%20shocks%20of%20demonetisation%20and%20the%20launch%20of%20a%20messy%20Goods%20and%20Services%20Tax.%20There%20is%20enough%20literature%20available%20to%20suggest%20that%20these%20events%20broke%20the%20back%20of%20micro%2C%20medium%20and%20small%20scale%20industry%20and%20helped%20the%20big%20corporates%20further%20consolidate%20their%20market%20share%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20small%20industry.%20In%20subsequent%20years%2C%20many%20large%20companies%20openly%20admitted%20%E2%80%93%20indeed%20touted%20%E2%80%93%20as%20their%20achievement%20that%20they%20had%20taken%20away%20substantial%20chunks%20of%20market%20share%20from%20the%20players%20in%20the%20small%20and%20unorganised%20sector%20who%20could%20not%20recover%20from%20these%20twin%20shocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20big%20companies%20further%20consolidated%20their%20market%20share%20through%202018%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20delivered%20another%20unprecedented%20advantage%20to%20corporate%20India%20in%20September%202019.%20He%20slashed%20the%20base%20corporate%20tax%20rate%20dramatically%20from%2030%25%20to%2022%25%20for%20existing%20companies.%20The%20government%20also%20reduced%20the%20tax%20rate%20from%2025%25%20to%2015%25%20for%20new%20companies%20that%20launched%20fresh%20capital%20investments%20projects.%20The%20finance%20ministry%20sacrificed%20about%20Rs%201%2C45%2C000%20crore%20by%20giving%20this%20concession%20to%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22What%20Needs%20to%20Be%20Disclosed%20by%20March%2031%3A%205%20Charts%20to%20Gauge%20the%20Cash%20Flow%20Through%20Electoral%20Bonds%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcharts-electoral-bonds-supreme-court-quashed%5C%22%3EWhat%20Needs%20to%20Be%20Disclosed%20by%20March%2031%3A%205%20Charts%20to%20Gauge%20the%20Cash%20Flow%20Through%20Electoral%20Bonds%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20finance%20ministry%20gave%20this%20massive%20incentive%20because%20new%20capital%20investments%20were%20not%20forthcoming%20from%20large%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20happens%20next%20is%20most%20interesting.%20By%20and%20large%20the%20corporate%20world%20did%20not%20fulfil%20the%20original%20intent%20of%20using%20the%20tax%20incentive%20to%20make%20big%20investments%20and%20generate%20employment.%20Instead%20most%20large%20companies%20use%20the%20big%20corporate%20tax%20cut%20of%202019%20to%20just%20add%20to%20their%20profitability%20without%20necessarily%20making%20any%20fresh%20investments%20in%20capacity%20expansion.%20In%20the%20subsequent%20four%20years%2C%20corporates%20would%20have%20roughly%20benefited%20by%20about%20Rs%206%20lakh%20crore%20from%20the%20tax%20cut.%20Well%2C%20after%20such%20a%20huge%20bonanza%2C%20buying%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20largely%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20ruling%20regime%2C%20should%20only%20be%20a%20logical%20next%20step!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20get%20a%20profit%2C%20and%20you%20get%20a%20profit%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20evident%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20top%2050%20to%20100%20companies%20listed%20on%20the%20stock%20exchange%20experienced%20a%20big%20boom%20in%20their%20profitability%20after%202019.%20There%20is%20data%20to%20suggest%20that%20the%20NIFTY%2050%20companies%E2%80%99%20combined%20profitability%20grew%20by%20under%205%25%20annually%20for%20many%20years%20before%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20post%202019%2C%20after%20the%20big%20corporate%20tax%20break%2C%20their%20profitability%20started%20growing%2015%25%20annually.%20By%202022-23%20the%20aggregate%20net%20profits%20of%20the%20top%20ten%20profitable%20companies%20listed%20on%20Nifty%20had%20grown%20beyond%20Rs%203%20lakh%20crore.%20The%20jump%20in%20profitability%20can%20be%20traced%20directly%20to%20the%20big%20corporate%20tax%20cut.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%202019%20onwards%2C%20the%20NIFTy%2050%20companies%20started%20to%20sparkle%20even%20in%20the%20stock%20markets%2C%20in%20anticipation%20of%20growing%20profits.%20Their%20turnover%20growth%2C%20however%2C%20largely%20stagnated%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20robust%20demand%20in%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20came%20Covid%20in%202020%20and%20the%20government%2FRBI%20came%20up%20with%20a%20slew%20of%20concessions%20%2C%20especially%20big%20cuts%20in%20interest%20rates.%20This%20again%20disproportionately%20benefited%20the%20large%20companies%20which%20retired%20more%20expensive%20debt%20with%20cheaper%20alternatives%20and%20managed%20to%20reduce%20interest%20costs%20substantially%2C%20again%20adding%20to%20their%20growing%20profits.%20The%20debt%20to%20equity%20ratio%20of%20large%20companies%20came%20down%20quite%20sharply%20during%20this%20period%20even%20as%20their%20stock%20prices%20continued%20to%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20larger%20point%20is%20government%20policies%20directly%20added%20to%20profitability%20of%20the%20top%20100%20plus%20companies.%20And%20during%20this%20period%20these%20companies%20may%20have%20generously%20bought%20into%20the%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20also%20a%20kind%20of%20quid%20pro%20quo%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20referred%20to%20while%20declaring%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20illegal%20and%20unconstitutional.%20Allowing%20companies%20to%20contribute%20unlimited%20amounts%20and%20yet%20affording%20them%20anonymity%20can%20hardly%20escape%20the%20charge%20of%20quid%20pro%20quo.%20Earlier%20there%20was%20a%20limit%20on%20how%20much%20companies%20could%20contribute%20to%20political%20parties%20from%20their%20profits%20and%20this%20was%20mandatorily%20declared%20in%20the%20annual%20report.%20But%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20did%20away%20with%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Electoral%20Bonds%20Scheme%20Violative%20of%20Voter%E2%80%99s%20Right%20to%20Information%3A%20Top%20Quotes%20From%20the%20Supreme%20Court%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felectoral-bonds-top-supreme-court-quotes%5C%22%3EElectoral%20Bonds%20Scheme%20Violative%20of%20Voter%E2%80%99s%20Right%20to%20Information%3A%20Top%20Quotes%20From%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWashing%20away%20black%20money%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWorse%2C%20some%20of%20the%20profits%20made%20by%20these%20companies%20may%20not%20even%20be%20directly%20used%20for%20buying%20electoral%20bonds.%20What%20if%20many%20of%20these%20companies%20have%20used%20benami%20route%20or%20shell%20companies%20to%20buy%20electoral%20bonds%3F%20During%20the%20arguments%2C%20the%20chief%20justice%20did%20ask%20this%20pertinent%20question%3A%20%E2%80%9CHow%20do%20we%20know%20that%20loss-making%20companies%20are%20not%20buying%20electoral%20bonds%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20shell%20companies%20are%20not%20meant%20to%20make%20profits%20and%20are%20used%20merely%20as%20vehicles%20to%20launder%20money.%20How%20do%20we%20know%20such%20companies%20have%20not%20been%20used%20to%20buy%20electoral%20bonds%3F%20Besides%2C%20promoters%20of%20companies%20which%20have%20defaulted%20on%20bank%20loans%20and%20have%20benefited%20from%20huge%20write%20offs%20(Rs%2014%20lakh%20crore%20under%20this%20regime)%20are%20still%20quite%20wealthy%20personally%20and%20may%20have%20bought%20electoral%20bonds%20through%20benami%20shell%20companies.%20How%20do%20we%20know%20this%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20happened%20on%20a%20significant%20scale%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20too%20many%20questions%20%E2%80%93%20none%20answered%20%E2%80%93%20in%20the%20pernicious%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme.%20Once%20the%20list%20of%20corporate%20donors%20is%20released%2C%20there%20will%20be%20some%20clarity.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708327845000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19125204%2Fpexels-photo-14907311.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fquid-pro-quo-how-revealing-electoral-bonds-will-clear-questions-of-len-den%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20demonetisation%2C%20big%20companies%20further%20consolidated%20their%20market%20share%20through%202018.%20PM%20Modi%20delivered%20another%20unprecedented%20advantage%20to%20the%20corporate%20India%20in%20September%202019.%20He%20slashed%20the%20base%20corporate%20tax%20rate%20dramatically%20from%2030%25%20to%2022%25%20for%20existing%20companies.%20The%20nation%20needs%20to%20know%20if%20any%20quid-pro-quo%20was%20involved.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A30%2C%22