w%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19095046%2Fshruti-singh-ilp4a4XCFUU-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20system%20of%20Minimum%20Support%20Prices%20(MSP)%20came%20into%20being%20in%20the%201960s%20and%20was%20supposed%20to%20provide%20an%20assurance%20of%20minimum%20remunerative%20prices%20to%20farmers%20with%20the%20promise%20that%20the%20government%20will%20purchase%20any%20quantity%20of%20farm%20produce%20that%20farmers%20are%20unable%20to%20sell%20at%20the%20minimum%20prices.%20However%2C%20this%20promise%20was%20never%20kept%2C%20and%20the%20system%20of%20government%20procurement%20was%20created%20only%20for%20a%20few%20crops%20and%20functioned%20only%20in%20a%20few%20states.%20This%20has%20become%20a%20major%20problem%20in%20the%20recent%20years%20as%2C%20in%20any%20given%20year%2C%20market%20prices%20for%20several%20crops%20prevail%20at%20levels%20that%20is%20far%20below%20the%20MSP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20demand%20for%20a%20guarantee%20of%20remunerative%20prices%20has%20emerged%20in%20this%20context.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20the%202014%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20Narendra%20Modi%20promised%20that%20if%20voted%20to%20power%2C%20his%20government%20will%20change%20the%20way%20MSP%20is%20set.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20will%20be%20a%20new%20formula%20%E2%80%93%20the%C2%A0entire%C2%A0cost%20of%20production%20and%2050%25%20profit%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20had%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2FPolitics%2FbYMbXRsL3eYQw2Bp4iMaXI%2FNarendra-Modi-promises-higher-support-price-to-farmers.html%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0What%20he%20was%20promising%20to%20implement%20was%20one%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Fpolicy%2Freport-summaries%2Fswaminathan-report-national-commission-farmers%5C%22%3Ekey%20recommendations%20of%20the%202006%20M.S.%20Swaminathan%C2%A0Commission%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0Ten%20years%E2%80%99%20into%20his%20time%20in%20office%2C%20though%2C%20this%20promise%20remains%20unfulfilled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20the%20ongoing%20farmers%E2%80%99%20struggle%20to%20press%20for%20the%20demand%2C%20a%20number%20of%20mainstream%2Fneoliberal%20commentators%20as%20well%20as%20editorials%20in%20the%20media%20have%20questioned%20the%20feasibility%20and%20wisdom%20of%20farmers%E2%80%99%20demand%20for%20a%20statutory%20right%20to%20MSP.%20These%20criticisms%20emanate%20from%20a%20neoliberal%20dogma%20about%20cutting%20welfare%20spending%20and%20turning%20the%20state%20into%20a%20facilitator%20for%20capitalists.%20It%20is%20precisely%20this%20perspective%20that%20lies%20at%20the%20root%20of%20the%20agrarian%20crisis.%20The%20purpose%20of%20this%20note%20is%20to%20dispel%20various%20myths%20being%20spread%20by%20these%20critics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20do%20farmers%20need%20a%20guarantee%20of%20MSP%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssured%2C%20remunerative%20prices%20are%20important%20not%20just%20for%20welfare%20of%20farmers%20but%20also%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20food%20security.%20For%20a%20large%20country%20like%20India%2C%20domestic%20production%20has%20to%20be%20the%20mainstay%20of%20food%20supply.%20As%20has%20been%20clear%20since%20the%201960s%2C%20dependence%20on%20imports%20for%20food%20grain%20not%20only%20makes%20India%20vulnerable%20to%20vagaries%20of%20international%20markets%2C%20it%20can%20force%20the%20country%20to%20compromise%20on%20its%20strategic%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarmers%2C%20like%20all%20other%20self-employed%20persons%20and%20businesses%2C%20do%20what%20is%20most%20profitable.%20But%20unlike%20other%20businesses%2C%20farmers%20face%20a%20particularly%20vexed%20problem.%20When%20they%20decide%20to%20sow%20a%20crop%2C%20they%20do%20not%20know%20how%20much%20the%20produce%20will%20sell%20for.%20Given%20the%20seasonality%2C%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20farmers%20sink%20a%20lot%20of%20resources%20in%20raising%20the%20crop%2C%20there%20is%20nothing%20they%20can%20do%20when%20the%20prices%20fall.%20Having%20incurred%20large%20expenses%2C%20and%20often%20in%20debt%2C%20few%20farmers%20can%20hold%20the%20produce%20and%20wait%20for%20prices%20to%20rise.%20This%20is%20a%20major%20cause%20of%20farm%20losses%2C%20debt%20burden%20and%20distress%20among%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Green%20Fields%2C%20Red%20Flags%3A%20Far-Right%20Authoritarian%20Tactics%2C%20Propaganda%2C%20and%20Alternative%20Reality%C2%A0%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fgreen-fields-red-flags-far-right-authoritarian-tactics-propaganda-and-alternative-reality%5C%22%3EGreen%20Fields%2C%20Red%20Flags%3A%20Far-Right%20Authoritarian%20Tactics%2C%20Propaganda%2C%20and%20Alternative%20Reality%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20can%E2%80%99t%20markets%20be%20allowed%20to%20determine%20equilibrium%20prices%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20many%20reasons%20why%20agricultural%20markets%20do%20not%20settle%20at%20equilibrium%20prices.%20Agricultural%20markets%20are%20notoriously%20imperfect.%20The%20number%20of%20producers%2Fsettlers%20is%20vast.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20often%2C%20a%20few%20large%20buyers%2Ftraders%20control%20the%20markets.%20This%20results%20in%20monopsonistic%20markets%20in%20which%20buyers%20exert%20undue%20influence%20over%20market%20prices%20and%20profiteer%20from%20it.%20This%20situation%20is%20made%20worse%20because%20farmers%20are%20often%20dependent%20on%20traders%20for%20finance%20and%20indebted%20to%20them.%20Also%2C%20individual%20farmers%20cannot%20predict%20either%20the%20conditions%20of%20demand%20at%20the%20time%20of%20harvest%20or%20the%20overall%20supply.%20Unpredictable%20weather%20conditions%20result%20in%20crop%20losses%20and%20supply%20shortages.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20there%20are%20years%20when%20a%20glut%20is%20caused%20because%20many%20farmers%20decide%20to%20grow%20a%20crop%20that%20was%20profitable%20in%20the%20previous%20year.%20Large%20businesses%20also%20have%20significant%20stocking%20capacity%20that%20they%20can%20use%20to%20sway%20market%20prices.%20For%20many%20crops%2C%20changes%20in%20supply%20conditions%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20world%20have%20an%20impact%20on%20domestic%20prices%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20these%20imperfections%2C%20agricultural%20prices%20fluctuate%20wildly.%20A%20crop%20that%20fetches%20a%20good%20price%20in%20one%20year%20sells%20for%20rock-bottom%20prices%20in%20the%20next.%20Farmers%20cannot%20predict%20prices%20when%20the%20decide%20to%20sow%20a%20crop%2C%20and%20often%20end%20up%20making%20huge%20losses.%20Once%20a%20crop%20is%20sown%2C%20farmers%20have%20little%20choice%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20these%20problems%2C%20agricultural%20prices%20should%20not%20be%20left%20to%20unregulated%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Ft24ACllNsd8%3Fsi%3DLvqRtG5sudMDphgS%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGovernment%20cannot%20buy%20and%20distribute%20all%20the%20produce%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20correct%20that%20government%20cannot%20procure%20and%20distribute%20all%20the%20agricultural%20produce%20and%20sell%20it.%20It%20is%20also%20correct%20that%2C%20in%20the%20current%20situation%2C%20if%20private%20buyers%20are%20forced%20to%20buy%20at%20a%20high%20MSP%2C%20this%20would%20be%20highly%20inflationary%20as%20they%20would%20pass%20the%20increased%20cost%20to%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20understand%20how%20this%20can%20be%20avoided%2C%20we%20need%20to%20understand%20why%20this%20situation%20has%20arisen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeoliberal%20policies%20adopted%20since%20the%201990s%20have%20resulted%20in%20a%20sharp%20rise%20in%20cost%20of%20cultivation%2C%20which%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20has%20broken%20down%20this%20synchronisation%20between%20public%20provisioning%20of%20agricultural%20inputs%20and%20services%2C%20agricultural%20price%20policies%20and%20food%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20neoliberal%20fixation%20with%20fiscal%20austerity%20and%20trade%20liberalisation%20has%20resulted%20in%20the%20reduction%20of%20state%20support%20to%20agriculture%20in%20the%20form%20of%20privatisation%20of%20supply%20of%20agricultural%20inputs%2C%20deregulation%20of%20input%20prices%2C%20power%20sector%20reforms%2C%20low%20public%20investments%20and%20low%20supply%20of%20formal-sector%20credit%20to%20agriculture.%20This%20has%20pushed%20up%20the%20cost%20of%20cultivation%20and%20made%20open%20market%20prices%20unremunerative.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20public%20procurement%20at%20MSP%2C%20which%20was%20meant%20to%20be%20a%20marginal%20operation%2C%20necessary%20only%20when%20market%20prices%20moved%20adversely%2C%20has%20become%20critical%20for%20farmers%20to%20not%20make%20losses%20in%20agriculture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20should%20not%20be%20required.%20The%20misalignment%20between%20open%20market%20prices%20and%20MSP%2C%20because%20of%20privatisation%20and%20deregulation%20of%20input%20prices%2C%20needs%20to%20be%20fixed%20by%20regulating%20the%20input%20costs.%20As%20per%20the%20Swaminathan%20Commission%20recommendations%2C%20MSP%20should%20be%20fixed%20at%201.5%20times%20the%20cost%20(commonly%20known%20now%20as%20%E2%80%98C2%2B50%25%E2%80%99).%20If%20cost%20of%20cultivation%20can%20be%20brought%20down%2C%20the%20MSP%20can%20be%20aligned%20closely%20with%20%3Cem%3Enormal%20%3C%2Fem%3Eopen%20market%20prices.%20This%20will%20ensure%20that%2C%20in%20any%20year%2C%20for%20most%20crops%2C%20market%20prices%20are%20remunerative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20such%20a%20situation%2C%20restrictions%20can%20be%20imposed%20on%20private%20buyers%20to%20not%20buy%20at%20prices%20less%20than%20the%C2%A0%20MSP%2C%20without%20this%20causing%20any%20significant%20disruption%20or%20inflation%2C%20and%20government%20will%20only%20need%20to%20procure%20those%20crops%20for%20which%20private%20traders%20are%20not%20willing%20to%20pay%20even%20the%20MSP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20guaranteed%20MSP%20will%20encourage%20cultivation%20of%20most%20profitable%20crops%20rather%20than%20those%20that%20are%20best%20suited%20to%20a%20region.%20This%20is%20ecologically%20disastrous%2C%20particularly%20for%20groundwater%20and%20soil%2C%20and%20bad%20for%20public%20health%20and%20food%20security.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarmers%2C%20like%20all%20other%20businesses%2C%20do%20what%20is%20most%20profitable.%20Why%20should%20they%20grow%20crops%20that%20are%20unprofitable%3F%20What%20is%20to%20guarantee%20that%20under%20free-market%20conditions%2C%20crops%20that%20are%20ecologically%20appropriate%20will%20be%20the%20most%20profitable%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20in%20a%20regime%20in%20which%20MSP%20applies%20to%20all%20crops%2C%20the%20government%20can%20ensure%20that%20crops%20that%20are%20ecologically%20most%20appropriate%20are%20also%20most%20profitable.%20The%20MSP%20can%20be%20set%20at%20a%20high%20level%20for%20crops%20that%20are%20ecologically%20appropriate%20and%20are%20important%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20nutrition.%20Free%20markets%20do%20not%20give%20a%20premium%20to%20these%20aspects.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20crops%20that%20are%20ecologically%20appropriate%20and%20nutritious%20are%20not%20profitable.%20The%20case%20of%20pulses%20and%20millets%20is%20well%20known.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20it%20is%20falsely%20argued%20that%20the%20MSP%20regime%20has%20incentivised%20farmers%20in%20Punjab%20to%20grow%20water%20intensive%20crops%20like%20paddy.%20The%20ecological%20problems%20of%20Punjab%20are%20not%20because%20paddy%20is%20covered%20under%20MSP%20and%20procurement.%20It%20is%20because%20other%20ecologically%20more%20appropriate%20crops%20are%20not%20covered%20under%20the%20MSP%20and%20procurement%20regime.%20There%20is%20nothing%20to%20ensure%20that%20millets%20and%20pulses%20are%20equally%20profitable%2C%20and%20the%20prices%20of%20these%20crops%20are%20not%20guaranteed%20through%20a%20system%20of%20procurement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20way%20farmers%20can%20be%20expected%20to%20adopt%20ecologically%20sustainable%20crops%20and%20farming%20practices%20is%20by%20making%20sure%20that%20these%20are%20also%20profitable.%20The%20MSP%20is%20a%20critical%20piece%20in%20that%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Why%20the%20American%20Argument%20Against%20India's%20Food%20Subsidies%20Is%20Deceptive%20at%20Best%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Findia-us-wto-minimum-support-price-food-subsidies%5C%22%3EWhy%20the%20American%20Argument%20Against%20India%E2%80%99s%20Food%20Subsidies%20Is%20Deceptive%20at%20Best%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20guaranteed%20MSP%20would%20be%20inflationary.%20A%20guaranteed%20MSP%20would%20make%20our%20farm%20products%20globally%20uncompetitive.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20inflationary%20impact%20has%20its%20roots%20in%20rising%20input%20costs.%20Prices%20of%20farm%20inputs%20have%20shot%20through%20the%20roof%20as%20a%20result%20of%20privatisation%20and%20deregulation.%20This%20needs%20to%20be%20checked.%20Input%20subsidies%20have%20to%20be%20for%20controlling%20prices%20of%20inputs%20and%20not%20for%20lining%20the%20pockets%20of%20seed%20and%20fertiliser%20companies.%20Government%20agencies%20should%20provide%20affordable%20inputs%20to%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20increases%20in%20the%20cost%20of%20cultivation%20can%20be%20contained%2C%20MSP%20will%20cease%20to%20be%20inflationary%20or%20become%20a%20barrier%20for%20agricultural%20exports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20agriculture%20is%20not%2C%20and%20should%20not%20be%2C%20primarily%20export-oriented.%20Growing%20water-intensive%20crops%20for%20exports%20is%20a%20bad%20idea.%20Shifting%20to%20export-oriented%20agriculture%20and%20compromising%20our%20own%20food%20security%20is%20a%20bad%20idea.%20Farmers%20should%20grow%20crops%20that%20are%20important%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20food%20security%20and%20are%20ecologically%20appropriate.%20For%20this%20to%20happen%2C%20cultivation%20of%20these%20crops%20has%20to%20be%20made%20more%20remunerative.%20This%20requires%20a%20guarantee%20of%20MSP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20government%20should%20direct%20resources%20towards%20safeguarding%20farmers%20against%20fluctuations%2C%20intervening%20when%20required.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20precisely%20what%20farmers%20are%20asking%20for.%20Having%20a%20system%20of%20MSP%20and%20procurement%20intervention%20is%20the%20way%20to%20ensure%20that%20markets%20give%20remunerative%20prices%2C%20and%20when%20they%20do%20not%2C%20the%20government%20steps%20in.%20That%20is%20the%20guarantee%20farmers%20are%20asking%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGovernment%20has%20been%20saying%20that%20they%20have%20already%20implemented%20the%20recommendation%20of%20the%20Swaminathan%20Commission%20regarding%20MSP.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Swaminathan%20Commission%20recommended%20that%20the%20MSP%20should%20be%20at%20least%2050%20per%20cent%20above%20the%20cost%20of%20cultivation.%20In%20the%20methods%20developed%20and%20used%20by%20the%20Commission%20for%20Agricultural%20Costs%20and%20Prices%2C%20the%20total%20cost%20of%20cultivation%20is%20called%20C2.%20But%20instead%20of%20fixing%20MSP%20at%20C2%2B50%25%20level%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20started%20using%20a%20lower%20cost%20called%20%E2%80%9CA2%2BFL%E2%80%9D%20as%20the%20benchmark%20for%20deciding%20MSP.%20A2%2BFL%20does%20not%20cover%20the%20entire%20cost%20of%20cultivation.%20It%20is%20much%20lower%20than%20the%20total%20cost%20actually%20incurred%20by%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20without%20a%20mechanism%20for%20enforcing%20the%20Minimum%20Support%20Price%20as%20a%20floor%20price%2C%20the%20MSP%20is%20nothing%20more%20than%20an%20empty%20promise.%20For%20most%20crops%2C%20MSP%20is%20just%20an%20announcement.%20There%20is%20no%20mechanism%20to%20ensure%20that%20farmers%20get%20that%20price%20for%20their%20produce.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERather%20than%20a%20guaranteed%20MSP%20for%20every%20crop%2C%20the%20government%20should%20offer%20support%20for%20the%20adoption%20of%20modern%20technologies%20for%20efficient%20and%20sustainable%20production.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENothing%20stops%20the%20government%20from%20giving%20a%20higher%20MSP%20for%20ecologically%20suitable%20crops%2C%20and%20providing%20support%20for%20improving%20efficiency%20and%20adoption%20of%20new%20technologies.%20Where%20is%20the%20contradiction%20with%20providing%20a%20guarantee%20of%20MSP%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInstead%20of%20a%20guaranteed%20MSP%2C%20the%20government%20should%20step%20up%20public%20investment%20in%20agriculture.%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%20the%20government%20needs%20to%20step%20up%20public%20investment.%20Why%20should%20a%20guarantee%20of%20MSP%20prevent%20the%20government%20from%20stepping%20up%20investment%3F%20Farmers%20are%20not%20asking%20for%20replacement%20of%20investment%20in%20agriculture%20with%20funds%20for%20procurement.%20They%20are%20asking%20for%20support%20for%20farmers%20through%20reduction%20in%20largesse%20and%20concessions%20given%20to%20corporates%2C%20not%20doing%20loan%20write-offs%20to%20corporates%2C%20and%20taxing%20the%20super-rich.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20small%20proportion%20of%20farmers%20in%20a%20few%20states%20corner%20all%20the%20benefits%20of%20MSP.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20MSP%20covers%2023%20crops%20which%20account%20for%20a%20small%20share%20of%20total%20value%20of%20agricultural%20output%20of%20India%2C%20and%20public%20procurement%20benefits%20a%20still%20smaller%20fraction%20of%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%2C%20however%2C%20the%20most%20important%20crops%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20food%20security.%20The%20government%20does%20not%20announce%20MSP%20for%20a%20number%20of%20high%20value%20commercial%20crops%2C%20livestock%20products%2C%20fish%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20system%20of%20procurement%20currently%20benefits%20only%20producers%20of%20rice%20and%20wheat%2C%20and%20that%20too%20only%20in%20a%20few%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20need%20to%20expand%20the%20guarantee%20of%20assured%20and%20remunerative%20prices%20through%20the%20system%20of%20MSP%20and%20public%20procurement.%20Some%20people%20may%20argue%20that%2C%20as%20a%20first%20step%2C%20the%20system%20of%20public%20procurement%20should%20be%20expanded%20to%20the%2023%20crops%20for%20which%20MSP%20is%20declared%20and%2C%20for%20these%20crops%2C%20to%20all%20the%20states.%20There%20is%2C%20however%2C%20no%20doubt%20that%20eventually%20all%20farmers%20should%20be%20provided%20a%20guarantee%20of%20remunerative%20prices%20for%20their%20produce.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20lot%20of%20growth%20in%20Indian%20agriculture%20in%20recent%20decades%20has%20come%20from%20sectors%20such%20as%20dairy%20and%20poultry%2C%20which%20are%20not%20covered%20by%20the%20MSP.%20This%20shows%20that%20MSP%20is%20not%20necessary%20for%20growth.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20possible%20that%2C%20for%20some%20commodities%2C%20markets%20provide%20remunerative%20prices%20in%20some%20years%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20production%20of%20these%20commodities%20sees%20a%20growth.%20But%20this%20does%20not%20happen%20for%20all%20crops%2C%20or%20at%20all%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20also%20be%20noted%20that%20the%20estimates%20of%20production%20for%20dairy%20and%20poultry%20are%20not%20as%20reliable%20as%20they%20are%20for%20the%2023%20%E2%80%9Cforecast%20crops%E2%80%9D%20for%20which%20MSP%20is%20declared.%20While%20estimates%20of%20production%20for%20%E2%80%9Cforecast%20crops%E2%80%9D%20are%20based%20on%20crop%20cutting%20surveys%20done%20every%20season%20in%20most%20states%2C%20the%20surveys%20for%20collection%20of%20data%20on%20production%20of%20these%20crops%20are%20not%20done%20systematically%20in%20most%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGrowth%20estimates%20for%20some%20of%20these%20commodities%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20overstated.%20For%20example%2C%20official%20statistics%20showed%20high%20growth%20for%20perishable%20commodities%20like%20milk%20even%20during%20the%20COVID%20period%20when%20producers%20of%20these%20commodities%20faced%20a%20severe%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20guarantee%20of%20MSP%20will%20not%20benefit%20the%20bulk%20of%20farmers%20who%20have%20small%20holdings%2C%20often%20working%20as%20farm%20and%20non-farm%20labour.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGuaranteed%20MSP%20is%20not%20a%20solution%20to%20all%20problems.%20But%20a%20more%20remunerative%20price%20does%20create%20conditions%20where%20farmers%20can%20pay%20better%20wages%20to%20farm%20workers.%20Remunerative%20agriculture%20is%20critical%20for%20the%20rural%20economy%2C%20including%20farm%20workers%2C%20and%20not%20beneficial%20only%20to%20large%20farmers.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20distress%20among%20farmers%20puts%20downward%20pressure%20on%20wages%2C%20depresses%20rural%20demand%20and%20slows%20down%20economic%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EVikas%20Rawal%20is%20a%20professor%20of%20economics%20at%20the%20Centre%20for%20Economic%20Studies%20and%20Planning%2C%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708324201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19095046%2Fshruti-singh-ilp4a4XCFUU-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%